Obligations of management officials

Management officials perform the obligations specified in Article 16, Article 17 of this Law and the following obligations:

1. To direct and organize the implementation of the tasks of the unit in accordance with the assigned responsibilities and authority;

2. Implementing democracy, preserving solidarity and professional ethics in the unit assigned to manage and in charge;

3. Responsible or jointly responsible for the implementation of professional activities of officials under the management and charge;

4. Building and developing human resources;effectively manage and use facilities and finance in the unit assigned to manage and in charge;

5. Organize the implementation of measures to prevent and fight corruption and practice thrift and combat waste in the unit assigned to manage and in charge.

Conditions for enrollment registration

1. People with all the following conditions regardless of ethnicity, men and women, social composition, beliefs and religions are registered to recruit officials:

a) Having Vietnamese nationality and residing in Vietnam;

b) From full 18 years of age.For some areas of cultural, artistic, physical training, sports, the admission age may be lower in accordance with the law;At the same time, there must be a written consent of the legal representative;

c) Having an application for admission;

d) Having a clear background;

d) Having a diploma, training certificate, practice certificate or talented skills suitable to the job position;

e) Good health to perform work or duties;

g) Meet other conditions required by the job position determined by the public non -business unit but not contrary to the provisions of law.

2. The following people are not allowed to register for officials:

a) Loss of civil act capacity or limited civil act capacity;

b) Being examined for penal liability;serving judgments and criminal decisions of the Court;Being applied administrative handling measures to be put into medical facilities, educational institutions, and reformatory schools.

Content and form of work contract

1. Working contracts with the following main contents:

a) Name and address of public non -business units and heads of public non -business units;

b) Full name, address, date, month, and year of birth of the recruited person.

In case the recruited person is a person under 18 years of age, the full name, address, date, month, year of birth of the legal representative of the recruited person;

c) Works or duties, job positions and working places;

d) Rights and obligations of the parties;

d) Type of contract, term and termination of work contracts;

e) Salary, bonus and other remuneration (if any);

g) Working time, rest time;

h) Practicing mode (if any);

i) Working conditions and issues related to labor protection;

k) Social insurance, health insurance;

l) The validity of the working contract;

m) Other commitments associated with the nature, characteristics of the industry, field and specific conditions of public non -business units but are not contrary to the provisions of this Law and other provisions of the relevant law..

2. The working contract is signed in writing between the head of the public non -business unit and the recruited person as an official and is made into three copies, of which one is assigned to the officials.

3. For professional titles in accordance with the law appointed by the superior of the head of the public non -business unit, before signing the working contract, it must be approved by that level.

Unilaterally terminate working contracts

1. Public non -business units are allowed to unilaterally terminate working contracts with officials in the following cases:

a) Officials with two consecutive years are classified and evaluated at the level of failing to complete the task;

b) Officials are forced to resign according to the provisions of Point d, Clause 1, Article 52 and Clause 1, Article 57 of this Law;

c) Officials working under an indefinite working contract with the term of sickness that has been treated for 12 consecutive months, officials working under the working contract with a definite term of sickness for 06 consecutive months.But the ability to work has not recovered.When the health of the recovery official is considered to sign the working contract;

d) Due to natural disasters, fire or other force majeure reasons as prescribed by the Government, the public non -business unit is forced to narrow the scale, making the job position that the official is undertaking no longer existing.;

d) When public non -business units terminate their operations under the decision of the competent authority.

2. When unilaterally terminating the work contract, except for the case specified at Point b, Clause 1 of this Article, the head of the public non -business unit must notify the officials at least 45 days in advance for the contractUnconfacement of term or at least 30 days for a definite working contract.For officials by the public non -business management agency, the unilateral termination of the working contract is decided by the head of the public non -business unit after the written consent of the written consent is in writing.of public non -business units.

3. The head of the public non -business unit must not unilaterally terminate the work contract with officials in the following cases:

a) sick or accidental officials, are treating occupational diseases under the decision of the medical facility, except for the case specified at Point c, Clause 1 of this Article;

b) Officials are taking annual leave, separate leave and other cases allowed by the head of public non -business units;

c) Female officers are during pregnancy, maternity leave, raising children under 36 months of age, except for cases of public non -business units to terminate their activities.

4. Officials working under indefinite working contracts have the right to unilaterally terminate the contract but must notify in writing to the head of the public non -business unit at least 45 days in advance;In case the sick or an accident has been treated for 06 consecutive months, it must notice at least 03 days in advance.

5. Officials working under a working contract with a definite term with the right to unilaterally terminate the contract in the following cases:

a) Do not be arranged in accordance with the job position, work location or not to ensure the working conditions agreed in the working contract;

b) Do not pay full salary or not pay on time under the working contract;

c) mistreated;forced labor;

d) Self or family really disadvantaged can not continue to perform the contract;

d) Pregnant female officers must quit their jobs as directed by the medical facility;

e) Sick or accidental officials who have been treated for 03 consecutive months but the ability to work has not recovered.

6. Officials must notify in writing the unilateral termination of working contracts for the head of public non -business units to know at least 03 days in advance for the cases specified at Points a, b,c, ƒê and e, Clause 5 of this Article;At least 30 days for the case specified at Point d, Clause 5 of this Article.

Please stop the position of manager or dismissal for managers

1. Management officers may resign from the position of management or dismissed if one of the following cases:

a) Not healthy enough;

b) Not enough capacity and prestige;

c) According to the task requirements;

d) For other reasons.

2. The management officer resigns to hold the position of management but has not been agreed by the head of the public non -business unit or the competent authority to resign from the position of management to continue performing the tasks and powers.mine.

3. The management officer after being resigned from the position of management or dismissal is arranged by the head of a public non -business unit or the competent authority is arranged in the position of work according to the working needs, in accordance with the professionalism.subjects and operations of officials.

4. The authority, order and procedures for consideration and decision to resign the position of management and dismissal of the management official shall comply with the provisions of law.

Content of official evaluation

1. The assessment of officials is considered according to the following contents:

a) Results of work performance or tasks under the signed working contract;

b) The implementation of regulations on professional ethics;

c) The sense of responsibility, attitude of serving the people, the spirit of cooperation with colleagues and the implementation of the Code of Conduct of Officials;

d) The performance of other officers' obligations.

2. The assessment of management officials is considered according to the contents specified in Clause 1 of this Article and the following contents:

a) Capacity of leadership, management, administration and organization of task performance;

b) Operation results of the unit assigned to be managed and in charge.

3. The assessment of officials is made every year;At the end of the apprentice;Before signing a work contract;change job position;Considering reward, discipline, appointment, re -appointment, planning, training and road compensation.

Classification of officials

1. Every year, based on the evaluation content, officials are classified as follows:

1. To successfully complete the task;

2. Complete tasks,

3. Complete tasks;

4. Do not complete the task.

Regime

1. When termination of work contracts, officials are entitled to severance allowances, job loss allowances or unemployment insurance regimes in accordance with the law on labor and the law on social insurance, except forThe case specified in Clause 2 of this Article.

2. Officials are not entitled to severance allowances if one of the following cases:

a) Being forced to resign;

b) Unilateral termination of working contracts that violate the provisions of Clauses 4, 5 and 6, Article 29 of this Law;

c) Termination of working contracts as prescribed in Clause 5, Article 28 of this Law.

State management of officials

1. The Government unified state management of officials.

2. The Ministry of the Interior is responsible to the Government to carry out the state management of officials and have the following tasks and powers:

a) Develop and promulgate according to its competence or submit to competent agencies to promulgate legal documents on officials;

b) To assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with ministries and ministerial -level agencies, planning and development plans and development plans to submit to competent authorities for decision;

c) Assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with ministries and ministerial -level agencies in promulgating the system of lists, standards and professional titles;

d) Manage statistics on public employees;guide the formulation and management of officials records;develop and operate the national database of officials;

d) Inspection and examination of state management of officials;

e) Annually, report to the Government on the contingent of officials.

3. The ministries and ministerial -level agencies within the scope of their duties and powers are responsible for performing the state management of officials.

4. People's Committees of provinces and centrally -run cities within the scope of their duties and powers performing the state management of officials.

Official manager

1. Content of official management includes:

a) Building a job position;

b) Recruitment of officials;

c) Signing work contracts;

d) Appoint and change career titles;

d) Change job position, seconded, terminate working contracts, resolve the regime;

e) Appointment and dismissal of management officials;arrange, arrange and use officials according to work needs;

g) Carry out the evaluation, commendation and discipline of officials;

h) Implementing salary regime, remuneration policies, training and retraining regimes;

i) Making and managing officials records;Follow the regime of reporting on management of officials under the management scope.

2. Public non -business units are assigned autonomy to implement the management contents specified in Clause 1 of this Article.The head of the public non -business unit is responsible for reporting to the superior on the situation of management and use of officials at the unit.

3. For public non -business units that have not been assigned autonomy, competent agencies manage public non -business units to manage public employees or decentralize the implementation of the management contents prescribed in the Clause1 This thing for public non -business units is assigned to manage.

4. The Government details this.

Discipline forms for officials

1. Officers violate the provisions of law in the process of performing jobs or tasks, depending on the nature and seriousness of the violation, they must be one of the following disciplinary forms:

a) reprimand;

b) Warning;

c) Writing;

d) Forced work.

2. Officials disciplined in one of the forms prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article may also be restricted to occupational activities in accordance with the relevant law.

3. Discipline methods only apply to management officials.

4. Disciplinary decision is saved to officials.

5. The Government stipulates the application of disciplinary forms, order, procedures and competence to discipline to officials.

Conversion between officials and officials and public servants

1. The conversion between officials and cadres and civil servants is implemented as follows:

a) The recruitment of officials to become civil servants must comply with the provisions of the law on cadres and civil servants.In case officials who have had time to work at public non -business units for full 5 years or more, they shall be transferred to civil servants without examinations;

b) The officials who are received and appointed to the job position prescribed by the law are civil servants, the decision to receive and appoint is also a recruitment decision;

c) Appointed officials holding positions in the leadership and management apparatus of public non -business units prescribed by law as civil servants are appointed to civil servant rank corresponding to the job position,The salary is entitled to the salary mechanism of the public non -business unit, which is kept the appointed career title, which is carried out in the provisions of this Law and other provisions of law.related;

d) Officers and civil servants are transferred to officials at public non -business units when meeting the conditions prescribed by this Law;

d) Civil servants in the leadership and management apparatus of the public non -business unit when the appointment term is not appointed but still continues to work at that public non -business unit, it is transferred as a tablet.function and arrange work in accordance with professional and professional;

e) The process of dedication, working time of officials before moving to cadres and civil servants and vice versa is considered when implementing contents related to training, retraining, reward and rights.Other benefits.

2. The Government details this.

The right to change them

1. Individuals have the right to request a competent state agency to recognize the change in them in the following case:

a) Change them for the biological child from the father of the mother to the family members of the mother or vice versa;

b) Change them to adopted children from their father or mother to their adoptive father or their adoptive mother at the request of the adoptive father and adoptive mother;

c) When the adopted child is adopted and this person or the father, the mother asks to regain them to that person according to the father of the father or mother;

d) Change them for children at the request of the father, mother or child when determining the father and mother for children;

d) Change the surname of the lost person has found his blood origin;

e) Change them with the family of their husbands and families in marriage and family relations with foreign elements to comply with the law of the country that foreign husband and wife are citizens or regain them before them beforechange;

g) Change their surname when their parents change them;

h) Other cases prescribed by the law on civil status.

2. The change of them for people from all over nine years or older must have the consent of that person.

3. The change of the individual's surname does not change, ending civil rights and obligations established according to the old family.

The right to change the name

1. Individuals have the right to request a competent state agency to recognize the change in the following case:

a) At the request of the person with the name, the use of that name is confusing, affecting the family affection, the honor, the legitimate rights and interests of that person;

b) At the request of the adoptive father, the adoptive mother about changing the name of the adopted child or when the adopted child is adopted and this person or the father, the mother asks to get the name that the father, the mother has ordered;

c) At the request of the father, mother or son when identifying the father and mother;

d) Changing the name of the lost person has found his blood origin;

d) Change the name of the husband and wife in the marriage and family relations with foreign elements to comply with the law of the country that foreign spouses are citizens or regain their names before changing;

e) Change the name of the person who has redefined the gender, the person who has transformed sex;

g) Other cases prescribed by the law on civil status.

2. The change of the name for the person from nine years or older must have the consent of that person.

3. The change of the individual's name does not change, ending the rights and obligations established by the old name.

The ward

1. The guardian includes:

a) Military people have no parents or mother or mother;

b) The minor has a father and mother, but the father and mother all lose civil act capacity;Father and mother all have difficulties in awareness and control of behavior;both parents are limited in civil act capacity;Father and mother are all declared to restrict their children;Father and mother do not have the conditions to care for, educate children and ask the guardian;

c) People who lose civil act capacity;

d) People with difficulties in awareness and control of behavior.

2. A person can only be guarded by a guardian, except for the case of a father and mother and guardian for children or grandparents, and her guardians.

The obligations of the guardian to the guardian who loses civil act capacity, who have difficulties in awareness and control of behavior

1. The guardian of the person who has lost civil act capacity has the following obligations:

a) Care and ensure the treatment of disease for the guardian;

b) Representing the guardians in civil transactions;

c) Managing the property of the guardian;

d) Protect the legitimate rights and interests of the guardian.

2. The guardian of the person who has difficulties in awareness and control of acts is obliged according to the decision of the Court among the obligations specified in Clause 1 of this Article.

The right of the guardian

1. The guardian of the minor, who loses civil act capacity with the following rights:

a) Using the property of the guardian to take care of and spend on the essential needs of the guardian;

b) Payment of reasonable expenses for the management of assets of the guardian;

c) Representing the guardian in the establishment and implementation of civil transactions and performing other rights in accordance with the law in order to protect the legitimate rights and interests of the guardian.

2. The guardian of the person who has difficulties in awareness and control of acts has the right to decide the Court among the rights specified in Clause 1 of this Article.

Change guardian

1. The guardian is changed in the following case:

a) The guardian no longer has the conditions specified in Article 49 and 50 of this Code;

b) The guardian is an individual who dies or is declared by the Court to limit civil act capacity, have difficulties in awareness, control behavior, lose civil act capacity and disappear;legal entities as guardians terminate existence;

c) The guardian seriously violates the guardian obligation;

d) The guardian proposes to be changed and someone else accepted as a guardian.

2. In case of changing the guardian of course, those who are prescribed in Articles 52 and 53 of this Code are natural guardians;If there is no guardian of course, the appointment and appointment of guardians shall comply with Article 54 of this Code.

3. Procedures for changing guardians shall comply with the law on civil status.

Termination of the guardian

1. The guardian ends in the following case:

a) The guardian has a full civil act capacity;

b) The guardian death;

c) The father and mother of the guardian who is a minor man who has eligible to exercise his rights and obligations;

d) The guardian is adopted.

2. Procedures for termination of guardians comply with the law on civil status.

Property management of the absent people at the residence

1. At the request of the person with related rights and interests, the Court assigns the property of the absent person at the residence to the following person to manage:

a) For properties that have been managed by the absent from the absence, the authorized person to continue managing;

b) For common property, the remaining common owner is managed;

c) For properties managed by the spouse, the husband and wife continue to manage;If the husband or wife dies or loses civil act capacity, has difficulties in awareness, controls behavior, is limited in civil act capacity, the adult children or parents of the absent people manage.

2. In case there are no people specified in Clause 1 of this Article, the Court shall appoint one of the relatives of the absent people at the residence to manage the property;Without relatives, the Court appointed another person to manage the property.

Declaration of death

1. People with related rights and interests may ask the Court to issue a decision to declare that one person is dead in the following case:

a) After 03 years, from the date of decision to declare the disappearance of the Court, it takes legal effect and still does not have the authentic news is still alive;

b) Specialized in the war after 05 years, from the end of the war and there is still no authentic news that is still alive;

c) Having an accident or disaster, natural disasters, after 02 years, from the date of the accident or disaster, that disaster ends, there is no authentic news that is still alive, unless otherwise provided for by law.;

d) Equipment for 5 consecutive years or more and there is no authentic news is still alive;This term is calculated according to the provisions of Clause 1, Article 68 of this Code.

2. Based on the cases specified in Clause 1 of this Article, the Court determines the death date of the person declared to be dead.

3. The decision of the Court declares that a dead person must be sent to the commune -level People's Committee of the residence of the person who is declared to die to take notes in accordance with the law on civil status.

Legal

1. An organization recognized as a legal entity when there are all the following conditions:

a) To be established in accordance with this Code, other laws are relevant;

b) Having an organizational structure as prescribed in Article 83 of this Code;

c) Having independent assets with other individuals and legal entities and self -responsibility by their property;

d) In the name of his own legal relationship independently.

2. All individuals and legal entities have the right to establish legal entities, except for other laws.

The charter of the legal entity

1. The legal entity must have a charter in case the law is prescribed.

2. The charter of the legal entity has the following main contents:

a) The name of the legal entity;

b) Purpose and scope of activities of legal entities;

c) Head office;Branches, representative offices, if any;

d) Charter capital, if any;

d) Legal representatives of legal entities;

e) Organizational structure;The formula for election, election, appointment, dismissal, dismissal, duties and powers of the titles of the executive agency and other agencies;

g) Conditions to become a member or no longer a member of the legal entity, if a legal entity has a member;

h) Rights and obligations of members, if a legal entity has a member;

i) Formula through decisions of legal entities;principles of internal dispute settlement;

k) The formula of amendments and supplements to the Charter;

l) Conditions for consolidation, merger, division, separation, formation of formal and dissolution of legal entities.

Dissolution of legal entities

1. The legal entity is dissolved in the following case:

a) According to the provisions of the Charter;

b) According to the decision of the competent state agency;

c) Expiring time limit shown in the charter or decision of a competent state agency;

d) Other cases as prescribed by law.

2. Before dissolution, legal entities must fulfill their property obligations.

Responsibilities for civil obligations of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam, central and local state agencies in civil relations with one side are state, legal entity and foreign individuals

1. The State of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam, the central and local state agencies are responsible for the civil obligations they have established by the State, legal entity and foreign individuals in case ofThe following:

a) International treaties that the Socialist Republic of Vietnam is a member who has provisions on abolishing immunity;

b) The parties in civil relations have agreed to abolish exemption rights;

c) The State of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam, the central state agency, in the locality abandoned the immunity.

2. Responsibilities for civil obligations of the State, state agencies when participating in civil relations with the State of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam, the central and local state agencies in the locality, Vietnamese legal entities and individuals are applied similar to Clause 1 of this Article.

Real Estate and Production

1. Real estate includes:

a) Land;

b) Houses and construction works attached to land;

c) Other assets associated with land, houses and construction works;

d) Other assets as prescribed by law.

2. Properties are non -real estate assets.

Conditions are effective of civil transactions

1. Civil transactions take effect when there are all the following conditions:

a) The subject has civil legal capacity, civil act capacity in accordance with civil transactions established;

b) The subject participating in civil transactions is completely voluntary;

c) Purpose and content of civil transactions do not violate the prohibition of the law, not contrary to social morality.

2. The form of civil transactions is a valid condition of civil transactions in case the law is prescribed.

Explain civil transactions

1. Civil transactions with unclear, confusing and understood content in many different meanings and not under the provisions of Clause 2 of this Article, the explanation of that civil transaction is done in the following order.:

a) According to the true will of the parties when establishing a transaction;

b) In the sense in accordance with the purpose of the transaction;

c) According to the practice where the transaction is established.

2. The contract explanation shall comply with Article 404 of this Code;The explanation of the will be implemented in accordance with Article 648 of this Code.

