Termination of contractual interference proposal

Proposal to interact with the following case:

1. The party is proposed to accept contracts;

2. The party is asked to answer without acceptance;

3. Expiring time limit for acceptance;

4. When notifying the change or withdrawal of the proposal takes effect;

5. When notifying the cancellation of the proposal takes effect;

6. As agreed by the requesting party and the proposed party within the time limit for waiting to be answered.

Content of the contract

1. The parties in the contract have the right to agree on the content of the contract.

2. The contract may have the following contents:

a) The object of the contract;

b) Quantity and quality;

c) Price, payment method;

d) Time, location and method of contract performance;

d) Rights and obligations of the parties;

e) Responsibility for contract violations;

g) The dispute resolution method.

Performing the contract when the circumstances change basically

1. Basic changes in the following conditions:

a) The change of circumstances due to objective causes occurred after contracting;

b) At the time of contracting, the parties cannot anticipate the situation changes;

c) The situation changes so greatly if the parties know before, the contract has not been concluded or concluded but with completely different content;

d) Continuing the contract performance without changing the content of the contract will cause serious damage to one party;

dd) The affected benefit party has applied all necessary measures in the permitted ability, in accordance with the nature of the contract that cannot be prevented and minimizing the level of affecting benefits.

2. In case the circumstances are fundamentally changed, the beneficiary has the right to request the other party to re -negotiate the contract for a reasonable time limit.

3. In case the parties cannot agree on the modification of the contract for a reasonable term, one of the parties may request the Court:

a) Termination of the contract at a definite time;

b) Amend contracts to balance the legitimate rights and interests of the parties due to the basic change.

The Court is only determined to amend the contract in case the termination of the contract will cause greater damage than the costs to perform the contract if the amended.

4. In the process of negotiation amending and terminating the contract, the Court resolves the case, the parties must continue to fulfill their obligations under the contract, except for other agreements.

Termination of contract

The contract terminates in the following case:

1. The contract has been completed;

2. According to the agreement of the parties;

3. Individuals who transferred a dead contract and legal entity to transmit the contract to terminate the existence that the contract must be implemented by the individual or legal entity;

4. The contract was canceled, unilaterally terminated;

5. The contract cannot be implemented because the object of the contract is no longer available;

6. The contract terminates as prescribed in Article 420 of this Code;

7. Other cases prescribed by the law.

Responsibility due to asset delivery in the wrong quantity

1. In case the seller assigns the property in more than the number of agreed, the buyer has the right to receive or not receive the reduction;If you receive it, you must pay for the reduction part at the agreed price in the contract, unless otherwise agreed.

2. In case the seller delivers less than the agreed quantity, the buyer has one of the following rights:

a) Receive the assigned part and determine the deadline for the seller to communicate the missing part;

b) Receive the assigned part and claim damages;

c) Cancellation of contracts and claims for damage if the violation makes the buyer fail to achieve the purpose of contracting.

Content of the cooperation contract

The cooperation contract has the following main content:

1. Purpose and term of cooperation;

2. Full name, residence of individuals;name and headquarters of legal entities;

3. Property contribution, if any;

4. Contribution by labor, if any;

5. Methods of dividing benefits and profits;

6. Rights and obligations of cooperative members;

7. Rights and obligations of the representative, if any;

8. Conditions for participation and withdrawal from members' cooperation contracts, if any;

9. Conditions to terminate cooperation.

