The right of the heritage manager

1. The heritage manager specified in Clauses 1 and 3, Article 616 of this Code has the following right:

a) Representing the heirs in relationships with a third person related to inheritance;

b) Enjoy the remuneration as agreed with the heirs;

c) Payment for heritage storage costs.

2. Persons who are possessing, using and managing heritage specified in Clause 2, Article 616 of this Code have the following right:

a) Continue to use the estate under the agreement in the contract with the person who left the heritage or the consent of the heirs;

b) Enjoy the remuneration as agreed with the heirs;

c) Payment for heritage storage costs.

3. In case of failure to reach an agreement with the heirs of the remuneration, the heritage manager is entitled to a reasonable remuneration.

People who are not entitled to heritage

1. The following people are not entitled to heritage:

a) The person convicted of acts of intentionally infringing upon their lives, health or serious abuse, torturing people leaving heritage, seriously infringing upon their honor and dignity;

b) The person who seriously violates the obligation to nurture the person leaving the heritage;

c) The person who is convicted of acts of intentionally infringes on the lives of other heirs in order to enjoy part or the whole of the heritage that the heir has the right to enjoy;

d) People who have deceived, forced or prevented people from leaving heritage in making a will;Forging wills, repairing wills, canceling wills, hiding wills to enjoy part or the whole heritage contrary to the will of the person leaving the heritage.

2. Those who specified in Clause 1 of this Article are still entitled to the heritage, if the person leaving the legacy knows the behavior of those people, but still gives them the heritage according to the will.

Content of the will

1. The will includes the following main contents:

a) Date, month and year of a will;

b) Full name and residence of the will;

c) Full name of people, agencies and organizations are entitled to heritage;

d) The heritage leaves and where there is a heritage.

2. In addition to the contents specified in Clause 1 of this Article, the will may have other contents.

3. The will not abbreviated or written by symbols, if the will consist of multiple pages, each page must be recorded in order number and signed or pointed by the will of the will.

In case the will with erasing and repairing, the person who writes the will or the testimony of the will must be signed next to the erasing and repairing place.

Cases of inheritance according to the law

1. Inheritance under the law is applied in the following case:

a) There is no will;

b) Legal wills;

c) The heirs according to the will die before or die at the same time as the will;Agencies and organizations are inherited according to the will no longer exist at the time of opening of inheritance;

d) Those who are appointed as an heir to a will without the right to be a heritage or refusal to accept the heritage.

2. Legal inheritance is also applied to the following parts:

a) The heritage is not decided in the will;

b) The heritage part is related to the will of the will not have legal effect;

c) The heritage is related to the inherited person according to the will but they have no right to enjoy the heritage, refuse to receive the heritage, die first or die at the same time as the will;Regarding agencies and organizations, they are entitled to a heritage according to the will, but no longer exists at the time of opening of inheritance.

Testament

1. The capacity to make a will, change or cancel the will be determined in accordance with the law of the country where the will of the will within the time of creation, change or cancellation of the will.

2. The form of the will is determined in accordance with the law of the country where the will was made.The form of the will also be recognized in Vietnam if in accordance with the law of one of the following countries:

a) The country where the will of the will reside at the time of making a will or at the time of the will of the will death;

b) The country where the will of the will be national at the time of making a will or at the time of the person who prepared the will die;

c) Water where there is real estate if inheritance is real estate.

Contract

1. The parties in the contractual relationship are agreed upon the application of the law applicable to the contract, except for cases specified in Clauses 4, 5 and 6 of this Article.In case the parties do not have an agreement on the law, the law of the country has the most linked relationship with that contract.

2. The law of the following water is considered the law of the country with the most associated relationship with the contract:

a) The law of the country where the seller resides if it is an individual or the place where it is established if it is a legal entity for the sale of goods;

b) The law of the country where the resident service provider if it is an individual or the place of establishment if it is a legal entity for a service contract;

c) The law of the country where the recipient of the residence is if an individual or the establishment where it is a legal entity for the contract of transfer of the right to use or transfer of intellectual property rights;

d) The law of the country where the employee regularly performs the work for the labor contract.If the employee regularly performs the work in many different countries or cannot identify where the employee regularly performs the work, the law of the country has the most linked relationship with the labor contract is the law.of the country where the employer resides for individuals or established for legal entities;

d) The law of the country where consumers reside for consumer contracts.

3. In case of proving the law of the country different from the law mentioned in Clause 2 of this Article, which is more linked to the contract, the law applied is the law of that country.

4. In case the contract with real estate objects, the law applies to the transfer of ownership and other rights to properties being real estate, renting real estate or the use of real estate forEnsuring the performance of obligations is the law of the country where real estate.

5. In case the law is selected by the parties in the labor contract, the consumer contract affects the minimum benefits of workers and consumers in accordance with the law of Vietnam, the law of VietnamApplicable.

6. The parties may agree to change the law to the contract, but that change is not affected by the legitimate rights and interests of the third person to be enjoyed before changing the law, exceptIn case the third person agrees.

7. The form of the contract is determined according to the law applied to that contract.In case the form of the contract is not consistent with the form of contracts according to the law applicable to that contract, but in accordance with the form of contract under the law of the country where the contract or the law of VietnamThat form of contract is recognized in Vietnam.

Transition terms

1. For civil transactions established before the effective date of this Code, the application of the law is prescribed as follows:

a) Civil transactions have not been implemented but have content and forms different from the provisions of this Code, the transaction subject continues to comply with the provisions of the Civil Code No. 33/2005/QH11 and the otherLegal documents detailing the Civil Code No. 33/2005/QH11, except for cases of the parties of civil transactions have an agreement on the amendment and supplementation of the content and form of the transaction for the transactionIn accordance with this Code and to apply the provisions of this Code.

Civil transactions are being implemented but with content and forms different from the provisions of this Code, the provisions of the Civil Code No. 33/2005/QH11 and legal documents prescribed expendituresDetailed Civil Code No. 33/2005/QH11;

b) Civil transactions have not been implemented or are being implemented but contains content and forms in accordance with the provisions of this Code shall apply the provisions of this Code;

c) Civil transactions are done before the effective date of this Code, but the dispute will apply the provisions of the Civil Code No. 33/2005/QH11 and legal documents specified in detail.Civil Code No. 33/2005/QH11 for settlement;

d) The statute of limitations is applied in accordance with this Code.

2. Do not apply this Code to appeal according to the procedure of cassation and re -examination for the case that the Court has resolved in accordance with the law on civilians before the effective date of this Code.

National education system

1. The national education system is an open and connected education system including regular education and continuing education.

2. The level of education, the training level of the national education system include:

a) Preschool education includes kindergarten education and kindergarten education;

b) General education includes primary education, lower secondary education and high school education;

c) Vocational training in primary level, intermediate level, college level and other vocational training programs;

d) Higher education for university level, master's degree and doctoral level.

3. The Prime Minister decided to approve the structure of the national education system and the national level of Vietnam;stipulate training time and standards for each level of training, minimum learning volume for the level of vocational education and higher education.

4. Minister of Education and Training, Minister of Labor, War Invalids and Social Affairs, within the scope of their duties and powers, stipulating the input threshold of college and university level under the industryTraining teachers and industry in the field of health.

Preschool education institutions

Preschool education institutions include:

1. Kindergarten and independent groups of children from 03 months to 03 years old;

2. Independent kindergarten and kindergarten schools accept children from 03 to 06 years old;

3. Kindergartens, independent preschool classes are educational institutions combining kindergartens and kindergartens, receiving children from 03 months to 06 years old.

Education level and age of general education

1. The education levels and the age of general education are stipulated as follows:

a) Primary education is carried out for 05 years, from grade one to the end of the fifth grade.The age of students in first grade is 06 years old and is calculated by year;

b) Secondary education is carried out for 04 years, from six to the end of the nine class.Students in the sixth grade must complete the elementary program.The age of students in the sixth grade is 11 years old and is calculated by year;

c) High school education is carried out in 03 years, from grade tenth to the end of the twelfth grade.Students in the tenth grade must have a secondary diploma.The age of the tenth grade is 15 years old and is calculated by year.

2. In case students are allowed to overcome classes and study at age than age as prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article, including:

a) Students study class in case of early development in intelligence;

b) Students at age are older than the prescribed age in the case of students who study the board and students in areas with extremely difficult socio -economic conditions, students are ethnic minorities and students.As a disabled person, students are underdeveloped in physical or intellectual, orphaned orphaned students, poor students, students from abroad to return to the country and other cases as prescribed by law.

3. General education is divided into basic education phase and career -oriented education phase.The basic education period includes elementary and junior high school level;The period of career -oriented education is high school level.Students in vocational education institutions learn the amount of high school cultural knowledge.

4. The Minister of Education and Training stipulates the teaching and learning of Vietnamese for children who are ethnic minorities before attending first grade;teaching the volume of high school cultural knowledge in vocational education institutions;The cases specified in Clause 2 of this Article.

