Duties and powers of the People's Procuracy when controlling the custody and temporary detention

1. The People's Procuracy Supervisores the compliance with the laws of agencies and people competent in custody and temporary detention.

2. When supervising the custody and temporary detention, the People's Procuracy has the following tasks and powers:

a) Directly supervise at temporary detention and detention camps;Ask people who are detained or detained on custody and temporary detention;

b) Control custody and temporary detention records;

c) Request the head of the temporary custody house and the supervisor of the detention center to inspect the custody and temporary detention and notify the results to the People's Procuracy;providing documents and documents related to custody and temporary detention;notify the situation of custody and temporary detention;Answering the decisions, measures or jobs that violate the law in custody and temporary detention;

d) Decide to release immediately to people in custody or temporary detention without grounds and illegal laws;

d) Forecasting, petitioning and requesting competent agencies and people in detention and temporary detention to suspend the implementation, amendment or abolition of decisions that violate the law in custody, temporary detention,terminating acts of law violations and requiring handling of law violators;

e) Prosecuting or requesting the investigating agency to prosecute a criminal case when detecting a case that shows signs of crime in custody and temporary detention in accordance with the law;

g) Settling complaints and denunciations and performing other duties and powers in the inspection of custody and temporary detention in accordance with the law.

Responsibility to fulfill the requirements, petitions, protests and decisions of the People's Procuracy in custody and temporary detention

1. Heads of temporary detention and supervisors are responsible for fulfilling the following requirements, petitions, protests and decisions of the People's Procuracy in custody and temporary detention:

a) Requirements for providing documents and documents related to custody and temporary detention must be implemented immediately;request to notify the situation of custody and temporary detention, request reply to decisions, measures or jobs violating the law in custody and temporary detention shall be implemented within 15 days;Request self -inspection of custody and temporary detention and notification of results to the People's Procuracy shall be implemented within 30 days from the date of receipt of the request;

b) The decision specified at Point d, Clause 2, Article 22 of this Law must be enforced immediately;If not agreed with that decision, it still has to be enforced, but there is the right to complain to the superior superior procuracy.Within 10 days from the date of receipt of complaints, the Head of the superior Procuracy must resolve;

c) Prestige specified at Point d, Clause 2, Article 22 of this Law must be resolved within 15 days from the date of receiving the protest;If not agreed with the protest, there is the right to complain to the superior superior procuracy;The superior Procuracy must be settled within 15 days from the date of receiving the complaint;The decision of the superior Procuracy is a legal decision.

2. For the proposal specified in Point d, Clause 2, Article 22 of this Law, competent agencies, organizations and individuals must consider, resolve and answer in accordance with the law on custody and temporary custodyprison.

Duties and powers of the People's Procuracy when controlling criminal judgment execution

1. The People's Procuracy supervisores the compliance with the laws of the Court, the criminal judgment enforcement agency, the agency and organization assigned a number of tasks of criminal judgment execution, competent persons, agencies, related organizations and individuals in criminal judgment execution.

2. When inspecting criminal judgment execution, the People's Procuracy has the following tasks and powers:

a) Request the Court to issue a criminal execution decision;request the Court, the criminal judgment enforcement agency, the agency or organization assigned a number of tasks to execute criminal judgments to self -examine the execution of criminal judgments and notify the results to the People's Procuracy;providing records and documents related to criminal judgment execution;

b) Directly control criminal judgment execution;Procurement of criminal execution documents.The People's Procuracy of the provinces and cities directly under the Central Government directly inspects the execution of prison sentences of the prison in the locality;

c) Decision to release immediately to people serving imprisonment sentences without grounds and illegal laws;

d) Proposing exemption, postponement, temporary suspension, suspension of serving sentences;Participate in the consideration and reduction of the judgment execution time limit, executing judicial measures, shortening the challenge time;

d) Obbur behavior and decision to violate the laws of agencies and competent people in criminal judgment execution;

e) Proposing and requesting agencies, organizations and individuals to terminate and overcome the law violations in the execution of criminal judgments;strictly handle violators;

g) Prosecuting or requesting the investigating agency to prosecute criminal cases when detecting a case that shows signs of crime in criminal judgment execution in accordance with the law;

h) Perform other duties and powers in criminal judgment execution inspection in accordance with the law on criminal judgment execution.

Settlement of complaints and denunciations in judicial activities under the authority of the People's Procuracy

1. The People's Procuracy competent to settle the following complaints:

a) Complaints of acts and procedural decisions of competent people of the People's Procuracy in the practice of prosecution rights and control of judicial activities;

b) Complaints of acts and procedural decisions of the heads of investigating agencies;Results of settlement of complaints of the heads of investigating agencies in the decisions and proceedings of investigators and deputy heads of investigating agencies;

c) Complaints of acts and procedural decisions of competent persons under the agency assigned to conduct a number of investigating activities;

d) Complaints in custody and temporary detention activities;

d) Complaints behavior, decision to manage and educate prisoners of persons assigned to manage and educate prisoners;

e) Other complaints as prescribed by law.

2. The People's Procuracy has the following authority to settle the following denunciations:

a) To denounce the law violation of the competent person of the People's Procuracy in the practice of prosecution rights and control of judicial activities;

b) denounce law violations in the activities of a competent person to conduct a number of investigating activities;

c) denounce law violations of competent persons in arresting, custody and temporary detention;

d) Den for law violations of the person assigned to manage and educate prisoners;

d) Other denunciations as prescribed by law.

3. When settling complaints and denunciations, the People's Procuracy has the following tasks and powers:

a) Receive, classify, accept, check and verify complaints and denunciations;

b) Request agencies, organizations and individuals to explain and provide relevant records and documents;

c) Applying necessary measures to prevent possible damage;

d) Make decisions on settlement of complaints and conclusions of denunciations;

d) Notify the decision on settlement of complaints and conclusions of denunciations to the person who has complained and denounced.

Organizational structure of the Supreme People's Procuracy

1. The organizational structure of the Supreme People's Procuracy includes:

a) The Procuracy Committee;

b) Office;

c) Investigation agency;

d) Departments, Departments, Institutes and equivalents;

d) Training and retraining establishments, press agencies and other public non -business units;

e) Central Military Procuracy.

2. The Supreme People's Procuracy has the Director, Deputy Director of the Supreme People's Procuracy, Procurators, Inspectors;Heads and deputy heads of investigating and investigators;Other civil servants, officials and other workers.

The Supreme People's Procuracy Committee

1. The Supreme People's Procuracy Commission includes:

a) Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy;

b) Deputy Director of the Supreme People's Procuracy;

c) A number of Supreme People's Procurats procurators decided by the National Assembly Standing Committee at the request of the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy.

2. The Supreme People's Procuracy Commission is held chaired by the Director to discuss and decide the following important issues:

a) Programs and working plans of the People's Procuracy industry;

b) Law projects, ordinances to submit to the National Assembly and the Standing Committee of the National Assembly;Reports of the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy submit to the National Assembly, the Standing Committee of the National Assembly and the President;

