Organizational structure of high -level People's Procuracy

1. The organizational structure of the high -level People's Procuracy includes:

a) The Procuracy Committee;

b) Office;

c) Institutes and equivalent.

2. The high -level People's Procuracy has the Head of the Senior People's Procuracy, the Deputy Director of the High -level People's Procuracy, Procurators, Inspectors, other civil servants and other workers.

The Supervisory Procuracy Committee

1. The Supervisory Procuracy Committee of the High -level People's Procuracy includes:

a) The Head of the Senior People's Procuracy;

b) Deputy Director of the Senior People's Procuracy;

c) Some procurators.

2. The number of members of the Procuracy and Procurators prescribed at Point c, Clause 1 of this Article is decided by the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy at the request of the Head of the High -level People's Procuracy.

3. The Procuracy of the High -level People's Procuracy is held by the Director to discuss and decide the following important issues:

a) The implementation of programs, working plans, directives, circulars and decisions of the Supreme People's Procuracy;

b) Summary reports of the high -level People's Procuracy;

c) Admission to the person working at the high -ranking People's Procuracy eligible for the examination of senior procurators, intermediate procurators, primary procurators;

d) Review and request the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy to re -appoint, dismiss and remove senior procurators, intermediate procurators, primary procurators working at the Supervisory InstituteSenior people.

