a) The Procuracy Committee;

b) Office;

c) Rooms and equivalent.

2. The provincial People's Procuracy has the Director, Deputy Director, Procurators, Inspectors, other civil servants and other workers.

Provincial People's Procuracy Commission

1. The Procuracy of the provincial People's Procuracy includes:

a) Director;

b) Deputy Director;

c) Some procurators.

2. The number of members of the Procuracy and Procurators prescribed at Point c, Clause 1 of this Article is decided by the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy at the request of the Head of the Provincial People's Procuracy.

3. The Provincial People's Procuracy Commission is held in the meeting by the Director to discuss and decide the following issues:

a) The implementation of programs, working plans, directives, circulars and decisions of the Supreme People's Procuracy;the implementation of the program and work plan of the high -level People's Procuracy;

b) Summary reports to the superior People's Procuracy, report to the People's Council of the same level;

c) Admission to people working at the provincial and district People's Procuracy eligible for the examination of senior procurators, intermediate procurators, primary procurators;

d) Review and request the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy to re -appoint, dismiss and remove senior procurators, intermediate procurators, primary procurators working at the Supervisory Instituteprovincial and district people.

4. The Procuracy Committee promulgates the Resolution when exercising competence in Clause 3 of this Article.The Resolution of the Procuracy must be approved by more than half of the total members;In case of equal voting, follow the director's opinion.If the Director does not agree with the opinions of the majority of members of the Procuracy, they shall comply with the decision of the majority, but the right to report to the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy.

5. At the request of the Head of the provincial People's Procuracy, the Procuracy discusses and comments on criminal cases, administrative cases, civil cases, marriage and family, and business, businessBusiness, trade, and labor for the Director to consider and decide.

Organizational structure of the Central Military Procuracy

1. The Central Military Procuracy belongs to the Supreme People's Procuracy structure.

2. The organizational structure of the Central Military Procuracy includes:

a) The Procuracy Committee;

b) Office;

c) Investigation agency;

d) Rooms and equivalent.

3. The Central Military Procuracy has the Director, Deputy Director, Procurator, Inspector;Heads, deputy heads of investigating agencies, investigators, other soldiers, civil servants, officials and other workers.

Central Military Procuracy Committee

1. The Central Military Procuracy Commission includes:

a) Director;

b) Deputy Director;

c) Some procurators.

2. The number of members of the Procuracy and Procurators prescribed at Point c, Clause 1 of this Article is decided by the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy at the request of the Director of the Central Military Procuracy.

3. The Central Military Procuracy Commission is held chaired by the Director to discuss and decide the following issues:

a) The program and work plan of the Military Procuracy;

b) Reports of the Central Military Procuracy of the Central Military Procuracy to the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy and the Minister of Defense on the work of the Military Procuracy;

c) Proposals of the Central Military Procuracy to the Minister of Defense on the fight against crime in the Army;

d) Admission to the person working at the Central Military Procuracy eligible to take the exam in senior procurators, intermediate procurators, primary procurators;

d) Review and request the Central Military Procuracy to submit to the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy to re -appoint, dismiss and remove senior procurators, intermediate procurators, procuratorsPrimary is working at the Central Military Procuracy.

