Evaluation, evaluation and approval of resource statements, oil and gas reserves

1. On the basis of the results of the exploration and jurisdiction of oil and gas, if the oil and gas is detected in the area of ‚Äã‚Äãoil and gas contracts, the contractor makes a statement of natural resources and oil reserves submitted to the Petroleum GroupMale reported the Ministry of Industry and Trade to appraise and approve.

2. The main contents of the resource and oil reserves report include:

a) History of search and exploration, quantity, development and exploitation of oil and gas;

b) DOCUMENTATION SEOSE SEASONS AND METHODS OF DELIVERY;drilling documents;survey documents and other research;

c) regional geology, mine geology;

d) Parametric parameters include geological formation of oil and gas, geophysical geophysics, mine technology, exploitation results, oil pressing pumps, gas and water (if any);

d) Calculating oil and gas on the initial spot, oil and gas reserves of oil and gas and petroleum detection;

e) Conclusion and recommendation.

3. The content of evaluation of resources and oil reserves includes:

a) Assess the results of the exploration and examination of oil and gas;

b) Geological rationality, geological model of pavement container, container parameters and mine technology;

c) The rationality and reliability of the initial petroleum calculation results and oil and gas reserves.

4. Vietnam Oil and Gas Group is responsible for monitoring, synthesizing resources, oil and gas reserves of oil and gas fields in Vietnam and updated annually information on resources and oil reserves reportingMinistry of Industry and Trade.

5. The contractor is responsible for updating the statements of the resources and gas reserves of each mine within 03 years from the date of oil, the first gas to be exploited and then updated for 05 years..In case the total amount of oil and gas on the first spot has changed more than 15% compared to the nearest approval, the contractor makes a report of resources and oil reserves updated to submit to the Vietnam Oil and Gas Group to report to the Ministry of Industry and Trade.Consider and approve in accordance with this Article.

6. The Government stipulates dossiers, order, procedures, appraisal and approval of resource and gas resources statements.

Establishing, evaluating and approving the Old Petroleum Development Plan

1. After the approved natural resource and reserves report, the contractor implements the stage of petroleum development and planning a general development of the oil and gas field to submit to the Vietnam Oil and Gas Group reporting.Ministry of Industry and Trade appraised and approved.

2. The main contents of the Overall Development Plan for Petroleum Development include:

a) History of searching, exploring and jurisdiction of petroleum, geological model of the mine and the Verification Plan at the next stage;

b) Mining technology and preliminary oil recovery coefficient;Expected development plans and selection plans;

c) Forecast of mining production and management output;

d) Preliminary design according to the selection development plans and preliminary determination of investment costs;

d) Drilling technology, drilling plan and finishing well;

e) Plan to implement environmental safety and protection;

g) Economic, technical assessment and selection of appropriate development plans at the time of reporting;

h) The main parameters and criteria of the option are selected as a basis for creating overall technical design;

i) Preliminary gas consumption plan;

k) Assess the level of technological risk, oil and financial fluctuations of the project;

l) Expected implementation progress;

m) For the Petroleum Development Project on the mainland, the Petroleum Development Project has a synchronous chain of works and petroleum equipment on the mainland and at sea, in addition to the contents prescribed inPoints A, B, C, D, D, E, G, H, I, K and L must have the following main contents in accordance with the law on construction: Preliminary demand for land use;demand for resource use;The conformity of the project with relevant strategies and plannings;assess socio -economic impacts, ensure national defense and security of the project;

n) Conclusion and recommendations.

3. The content of appraising the general plans for petroleum development includes:

a) Assess the conformity of mine technology, forecasting output and preliminary oil recovery coefficient;

b) Assess the conformity of expected development plans and options for drilling technology and exploitation technology;The main parameters and criteria of the plan are selected as a basis for creating overall technical design;

c) Assess the meeting of safety and environmental protection requirements;

d) Rationality in preliminary evaluation of economic and technical efficiency;level of technological risk, product price fluctuations and finance of the project;

d) Assess the conformity with the relevant plans;

e) The content of evaluation in accordance with the law on construction for the contents specified at Point m, Clause 2 of this Article.

4. The preparation, evaluation and approval of the Oil Petroleum Development Plan instead of the formulation, appraisal and approval of the pre -feasibility study report of construction investment projects of the Petroleum Project in accordance with the Law.Build.

5. When changing the development plan, the demand for land use (if any), the gas consumption plan in the general mine development plan plan, the contractor submits it to the Vietnam Oil and Gas GroupThe Ministry of Industry and Trade shall consider and approve the adjustment of the Old Petroleum Development Plan.The adjustment of other contents of the General Plan for the Development of Petroleum Development is considered and approved by the Vietnam Oil and Gas Group.

6. The Government stipulates the dossiers, order, procedures for submission, evaluation and approval of the Oil Petroleum Development Plan.

