The order and procedures for conducting an administrative inspection

1. Prepare inspection, including the following steps:

a) Collect information to prepare inspection;

b) Promulgating inspection decisions;

c) Develop and submit an outline to request the inspection subject;

d) Notice of the announcement of inspection decisions.

2. Conduct direct inspection, including the following steps:

a) Announcing inspection decisions;

b) Collect information and documents related to the inspection content;

c) Checking and verifying information and documents;

d) End of direct inspection.

3. End of the inspection, including the following steps:

a) Report inspection results;

b) Develop an inspection conclusions;

c) Evaluation of the draft inspection conclusions;

d) Promulgating inspection conclusions;

d) Publicly inspection conclusions.

