Handling overlapping and duplicating in inspection activities

1. When conducting inspection and state audit activities, if detected overlapping, duplicating, the inspection agency coordinates with the State Audit Agency to handle according to the provisions of the State Audit Law andThis law, ensuring an activity content of organizations and individuals is only the object of an inspection agency or state audit agency.

2. overlapping, duplicating in activities between inspection agencies are handled as follows:

a) Overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the Government Inspectorate and other inspection agencies, the Government Inspectorate conducted inspections;

b) Overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the Ministry Inspectors, the Chief Inspectors of the Ministry of Exchange for handling;In case of inconsistency, the Government Inspector General shall consider and decide;

c) overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the Ministry Inspectorate and the provincial Inspectorate, the Department Inspectorate or the District Inspectorate, the Chief Inspector of the Ministry exchanged with the Chief Inspector of the province, Chief Inspector of the Department or the District Chief Inspector to handlephysical;In case of inconsistency, the Ministry Inspectorate conducts inspection;

d) A overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the Ministry Inspectorate or the General Department Inspectorate, the Department and the Inspection Agency of the Government Agency, the Chief Inspector of the Ministry exchanged with the head of the inspection agency of the agencyGovernment for handling;In case of inconsistency, the Chief Inspector of the Ministry reports to the Government Inspector General for consideration and decision;

d) overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the inspection agency of the Government agency and the provincial Inspectorate, the Department Inspectorate or the District Inspectorate, the heads of the inspection agency of the Government's agency exchanged with the ChiefInvestigate the province, Chief Inspector of the Department or the District Chief Inspector to handle;In case of inconsistency, the inspection agency of the Government agency conducts inspection;

e) overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the General Department Inspectorate, the Department of the Provincial Inspectorate, the Department Inspectorate or the District Inspectorate, the Chief Inspector of the General Department, the Department exchanged with the Chief Inspector of the province, the Chief Inspector of the Department orDistrict Chief Inspector for handling;In case of inconsistency, the Inspectorate of the General Department and Department shall conduct inspection;

g) overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the General Department inspectors, the Department in the same ministry, the Chief Inspector of the General Department and the Department of Exchange for handling;In case of inconsistency, it is reported to the Ministry of Inspectorate for consideration and decision;

h) A overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the provincial Inspectorate and the Department Inspectorate or the District Inspectorate, the Chief Inspector of the Inspectorate exchanged with the Chief Inspector of the Department or the District Chief Inspector to handle;In case of inconsistency, the provincial inspection conducts inspection;

i) overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the Department Inspectors, the Chief Inspectors of the Department exchanged for handling;In case of inconsistency, the provincial Chief Inspector shall consider and decide;

k) overlapping and duplicating between the activities of the Department Inspectorate and the district inspection, the Chief Inspector of the Department exchanged with the District Chief Inspector for handling;In case of inconsistency, the Department Inspectorate conducts inspection;

l) The overlapping and duplicating handling between the activities of the inspection agency of the administrative - economic unit especially with other inspection agencies prescribed by the Government Inspector General when the administrative - economic unitEspecially established.

3. The overlapping and duplicating handling arising in the operation of the inspection agencies is not under the cases specified in Clause 2 of this Article, which is prescribed or considered and handled by the Government Inspector General.

Re -inspection

1. The inspection is done when there is one of the following bases:

a) There are serious violations of the order and procedures in the process of conducting inspection;

b) There is a mistake in applying the law when the inspection conclusions;

c) The content of the inspection conclusions is not consistent with the evidence collected during the inspection process;

d) The person conducts the inspection intentionally falsify the case file or intentionally concluding the law;

dd) Short signs of serious law violations of the inspection subjects but have not been fully detected through inspection.

2. The statute of limitations for inspection is 02 years from the date of signing the inspection conclusion.

3. Conclusion of the inspection must have contents as prescribed in Clause 2, Article 78 of this Law and must clearly define the responsibilities of the inspection agency and the inspection person of the previous inspection.

4. The Government details this.

Promulgating inspection decisions

1. Heads of inspection agencies shall base on Article 51 of this Law to promulgate inspection decisions.

2. The inspection decision includes the following contents:

a) Bases on inspection decisions;

b) Scope, contents, subjects, inspection periods, inspection tasks;

c) Inspection term;

d) Establishing an inspection team, including the head of the inspection team, the Deputy Head of the Inspection Team (if any), another member of the Inspection Team.

3. For planning inspections, the inspection decision must be sent to the inspection subjects and published within 15 days before the direct inspection.

4. For unexpected inspections, the inspection decision must be sent to the inspection subjects and published before conducting the inspection directly, except for the case specified in Clause 3, Article 64 of this Law.

Develop and disseminate the inspection plan

1. The Head of the Inspection Delegation shall assume the prime responsibility for, and submit the inspection plan and submit it to the inspection decision for approval.

2. The inspection plan includes the following contents:

a) Purpose and requirements;

b) Scope, content, subjects, inspection period, inspection term;

c) Inspection methods;

d) Implementation progress;

d) Information and reporting regime;

e) The use of vehicles, funding and other material conditions for the inspection team's activities.

3. The head of the inspection team held an inspection team meeting to disseminate the plan to conduct inspections and assign tasks to members of the inspection team.

Suspension of inspection

1. The inspection decision makers decided to suspend the inspection in the following cases:

a) The subject of the inspection is the dead individual;Agencies and organizations have been dissolved or bankrupt without any agencies, organizations and individuals inheriting the rights and obligations;

b) The contents of the inspection have been concluded by the superior inspection agency;

c) The investigating agency has issued a decision to prosecute a criminal case on the same inspection content;

d) Heads of state management agencies of the same level shall request a written request for suspension of the inspection;

d) In the case of overlapping and duplicating, it has been handled in accordance with Article 55 of this Law.

2. When suspending the inspection, the inspection person is responsible for canceling the measures applied according to its competence during the inspection process.

3. The decision to suspend the inspection must be sent to the inspection subjects.

Report on inspection results

1. After finishing the direct inspection, the Head of the Inspection Delegation shall develop a report on the inspection results to the inspection decision maker.The inspection results report must have the following contents:

a) Specific conclusions about each inspection;

b) Clearly define the nature, extent and consequences of violations;Causes and responsibilities of agencies, organizations and individuals committing violations of law (if any);

c) Different opinions (if any) between other members of the inspection team and the Head of the Inspection Delegation on the contents of the inspection results report;

d) Handling measures have been applied and recommend solutions, measures to handle and remedy consequences (if any).

2. In case the inspection detects corruption and negative acts, the inspection results report must also clearly state the responsibilities of the heads of the agency or organization to occur acts of corruption and negativity.According to the following levels:

a) Weakness in management capacity;

b) Lack of responsibility in management;

c) Covering people with corrupt and negative acts.

3. Reporting inspection results must clearly state the provisions of law as a basis to determine the nature, seriousness of violations, proposals of solutions, measures to handle and remedy consequences.

4. Time to develop the inspection results from the date the inspection team ends the conduct of direct inspection and are prescribed as follows:

a) For the inspection conducted by the Government Inspectorate, the time to develop the report on the inspection results shall not exceed 30 days, the complicated case may last but not more than 45 days;

b) For the inspection by the Ministry Inspectorate, the General Department's Inspectorate, the Department, the Provincial Inspectorate, the time to develop the inspection results report for no more than 20 days, the complicated case may be extended butNot more than 30 days;

c) For the inspection conducted by the Department Inspectorate and District Inspectorate, the time to develop the report on the inspection results shall not exceed 15 days, the complicated case may last but not exceeding 20 days.

