Publicly inspection conclusions

1. At least 10 days from the date of signing the inspection conclusions, the inspection decision maker has the responsibility to publicly conclude the inspection conclusions in the form specified at Point a, Clause 3 of this Article and one of the pictures.The provisions of points b, c and d, Clause 3 of this Article.

2. Inspection conclusions must be publicized, except for contents of state secrets or other secrets in accordance with the Law.

3. The form of public inspection conclusions includes:

a) Post on the web portal of the inspection agency or state management agency of the same level;

b) Organize a meeting to announce the inspection conclusions with ingredients including inspection decisions, inspection teams, inspection subjects, relevant agencies, organizations and individuals or organize press conferences;

c) Notice on at least one mass media.For the inspection by the Government Inspectorate, the Ministry Inspectorate, the General Department Inspectorate and the Department, the Department shall notify on a mass media at the central level;For inspections conducted by the provincial inspection, the Department Inspectorate, the district inspection, the notice on a local mass media;

d) Listed at the working offices of agencies and organizations that are inspection subjects.

4. The Government details this.

Tasks and powers of the inspection decision maker

1. The inspection decision makers are responsible for the following tasks and powers:

a) Direct, inspect and supervise the inspection team to comply with the contents of the inspection decision;

b) Request the subjects to provide information, documents and reports, explain the issues related to the inspection content;Request relevant agencies, organizations and individuals to provide information and documents on the inspection content;

c) Decide on the solicitation of assessment on issues related to the inspection content;

d) Decide or request a competent person to decide to temporarily seize assets, licenses, and practice certificates that are illegally used;

d) Suspend or propose competent persons to suspend violations;

e) Request credit institutions to block accounts of the inspection subject;Proposing assets, income and other agencies to take measures to promptly prevent inspection subjects that have acts of destroying, dispersing property or to ensure the implementation of the Revenue DecisionProperty of heads of inspection agencies, heads of state management agencies;

g) Decision on asset inventory;

h) Decision on recovery of property appropriated, occupied, illegally used or lost;

i) Proposing a person to suspend the implementation of disciplinary decisions, transferring work, quitting, retiring for inspection subjects or information providers and documents on the contents of inspection.If there is a basis to think that the implementation of that decision interfere with inspection activities;

k) Proposing the competent person to suspend the work and handling of cadres, civil servants and public employees intentionally obstructing the inspection activities or failing to comply with the requirements, petitions and inspection decisions;

l) Decision on handling according to its competence or proposing a competent person to handle inspection results;inspect and urge the implementation of inspection decisions;

m) Settling complaints, denunciations, petitions and reflections related to the responsibility of the Head of the Inspection Team and other members of the Inspection Team;

n) Suspension, change the head of the inspection team, other members of the inspection team;

o) Promulgating inspection conclusions;

p) Transfer the case and documents related to the written petition to the investigating agency when detecting signs of criminals as prescribed in Clause 3, Article 68 of this Law;

q) sanction administrative violations according to its competence;

r) Perform other duties and powers as prescribed by the Law.

2. When the application of measures prescribed at points d, dd, e, i and k, Clause 1 of this Article is no longer necessary, the inspection decision makers must decide or propose to immediately cancel the applicationthat dharma.

Tasks and powers of the Head of the Inspection Delegation

1. The leader of the inspection team has the following tasks and powers:

a) Organize and direct members of the inspection team to comply with the contents of the inspection decision;

b) Proposing the inspection decision makers to apply measures under the jurisdiction in accordance with this Law and the other relevant law provisions to ensure the implementation of the requirements and purpose of inspection;

c) Requesting the subjects to provide information, documents and reports, explanation on issues related to the inspection content;Request relevant agencies, organizations and individuals to provide information and documents on the inspection content;

d) Request and request the competent person to decide on the temporary seizure of properties, licenses and practicing certificates that are illegally used;request competent agencies to temporarily seize inventory properties;

d) Request credit institutions to block accounts of inspection subjects;Proposing assets and income control agencies and other competent agencies to take measures to promptly prevent inspection subjects that have acts of destroying and dispersing property;

e) Decision on sealing documents;

g) Decision on asset inventory;

h) suspend or propose competent people to suspend violations;

i) Proposing a person to suspend the implementation of disciplinary decisions, transferring work, quitting, retiring for inspection subjects or information providers and documents on the contents of inspection.If there is a basis to think that the implementation of that decision interfere with inspection activities;

k) Sanction administrative violations according to its competence;

l) Report the inspection decision on the inspection results and take responsibility for the accuracy, honesty and objectivity of that report;

m) Perform other duties and powers as prescribed by the Law.

2. When the application of measures prescribed at points d, dd, e, h and i, Clause 1 of this Article is no longer necessary, the inspection team leader must decide or propose to immediately cancel the application of that measure..

Duties and powers of other members of the inspection team

1. Other members of the inspection team are the following tasks and powers:

a) Perform the task as assigned by the Head of the Inspection Delegation;

b) Request the subjects to provide information, documents and reports, explain the issues related to the inspection content;Request relevant agencies, organizations and individuals to provide information and documents on the inspection content;

c) Sanction administrative violations according to its competence;

d) Proposing the Head of the Inspection Delegation to apply the measures and powers of the Head of the Inspection Delegation specified in Clause 1, Article 81 of this Law to ensure the performance of the assigned tasks;

d) To report to the head of the inspection team for the results of the assigned tasks, take responsibility to the head of the inspection team and before the law for the accuracy, honesty and objectivity of the reported content;

e) Perform other duties and powers as prescribed by the Law.

2. Other members of the inspection team are not the inspectors who have the tasks and powers prescribed at Points a, d, dd and e, Clause 1 of this Article.

Rights of the inspection object

1. Inspectors have the following right:

a) Explanation on issues related to the inspection content;

b) Complaints about the decision and behavior of the inspection person during the inspection process;Complaints for handling decisions on inspection in accordance with the law on complaints;propose the content in the inspection conclusions when it is that the content is not accurate;

c) claim damages, restore other legitimate rights and interests in accordance with law.

2. Individuals who are the subjects have the right to denounce the law violations of the inspection person in accordance with the law on denunciations.

Duties and powers of supervisors

1. Develop a plan to monitor the inspection decision for approval.

2. Working with inspection teams and agencies, organizations and individuals related to the supervision content.The monitoring person only works with the inspection subjects at the request of the inspection decision maker.

3. Request the following inspection team to provide information and documents:

a) Decision on inspection, decision to extend the time limit for inspection, decision to suspend, change the head of the inspection team, other members of the inspection team, decide to amend and supplement the contentsconduct inspections and proposals to request the inspection subjects, the guiding documents of the inspection decision maker;

b) Report on the performance of other members of the inspection team with the Head of the Inspection Delegation and the Head of the Inspection Delegation to the inspection decision maker;

c) Complaints, denunciations, petitions and feedbacks related to the activities of the inspection team (if any);

d) Other documents under the direction of the inspection decision.

4. Reporting the inspection decision on the content of the inspection team's operation plan and other contents at the request of the inspection decision maker;In case the inspection team's operation is not in accordance with the inspection plan or detecting prohibited behavior in the inspection activities of the Head of the Inspection Team and other members of the inspection team, the decision maker must be reported toInspection plan for handling in accordance with law.

Responsibilities of the inspection subjects, heads of agencies, direct management of inspection subjects and relevant agencies, organizations and individuals

1. Inspection subjects must fulfill the inspection conclusions fully, promptly and on time.

Regarding the contents of the inspection conclusions that have not been implemented immediately, within 10 days from the date of public conclusions, the inspection subject must develop a plan to implement the inspection conclusions submitted to the personauthority, which clearly states the progress and explains the reason.

2. Within 15 days from the date of publicization of inspection conclusions, based on the contents in the inspection conclusions, the written organization of the inspection conclusions, requirements, petitions and handling decisions onInspectors, heads of agencies, direct management organizations are responsible for the following responsibilities:

a) Completely, timely and timely implementation, petitions and handling decisions on inspections within the scope of their responsibilities;

b) Timely direct the inspection subjects to organize the implementation of inspection conclusions, requirements, petitions and handling decisions on inspection;

c) Apply measures according to its competence to address difficulties and obstacles of the inspection subjects in the process of implementing inspection conclusions, requirements, petitions and handling decisions on inspection;

d) Check the formulation of the inspection conclusions of the inspection subject.

3. Inspection subjects, heads of agencies, direct management organizations subjects and relevant agencies, organizations and individuals are responsible for reporting the results of the inspection conclusions to the inspection conclusion to the levelcompetent and heads of inspection agencies.

Domestic violence

1. Domestic violence acts include:

a) Torturing, mistreating, beating, threatening or other intentional acts to abuse health and life;

b) Instant, lead or other intentional acts insulting honor and dignity;

c) Forced to witness violence against people and animals in order to put frequent psychological pressure;

d) Leave and care;Do not nurture and take care of family members who are children, pregnant women, women who are raising children under 36 months of age, elderly people, people with disabilities, people who are unable to take care of themselves;do not educate family members as children;

d) Discrimination and discrimination of physical shape, gender, gender and capacity of family members;

e) Prevent family members from meeting relatives, have legal, healthy social relations or other behaviors in order to isolate and put frequent psychological pressure;

g) Prevent the exercise of rights and obligations in family relationships between grandparents and grandchildren;between father, mother and child;between husband and wife;between siblings and sisters;

h) Revealing or distributing information about private life, personal secrets and family secrets of family members to insult the honor and dignity;

i) Forced to perform acts of contradictory sex of spouse;

k) Forced to perform porn behavior;Forced sound, view images, read pornography, stimulate violence;

l) Forced child marriage, marriage, divorce or obstructing marriage, legal divorce;

m) Forced pregnancy, abortion, fetal sex selection;

n) appropriate and destroy the common property of the family or private property of other family members;

o) Forcing family members to study, overwork, and contribute their financial contributions;Control assets and income of family members in order to create physical, mental or other aspects;

p) Isolate and detain family members;

Q) Forced family members out of illegal legal accommodation.

2. The acts specified in Clause 1 of this Article shall be performed between the divorced person;people living as husband and wife;He is a father, mother, stepchild, siblings, and younger sisters who have divorced, of the people living as husband and wife;People who have had a adopted parents' relationship with each other are also identified as a domestic violence in accordance with the Government's regulations.

International cooperation on domestic violence prevention and control

1. International cooperation on domestic violence prevention and control is implemented on the principle of equality, respect for independence and sovereignty, in accordance with Vietnamese law and international law.

2. Contents of international cooperation on domestic violence prevention and control include:

a) Participate in international organizations;signing and implementing international treaties and international agreements on domestic violence prevention and control;

b) Develop and implement programs, projects and activities on domestic violence prevention and control;

c) Exchange of information and experience on domestic violence prevention and control;

d) Scientific research, human resource training on domestic violence prevention and control.

Rights and responsibilities of people with domestic violence

1. People with domestic violence have the following rights:

a) Requesting competent agencies, organizations and individuals to protect health, life, honor, dignity, other legitimate rights and interests related to domestic violence;

b) Request competent agencies and individuals to apply measures to prevent, protect and support in accordance with this Law;

c) To be arranged in a temporary place, keep a secret about the temporary shelter and information about private life, personal secrets and family secrets in accordance with this law and other relevant laws.;

d) Be provided with medical services, psychological advice, skills to respond to domestic violence, legal aid and social assistance in accordance with the law;

dd) Request those who commit domestic violence to overcome the consequences and compensate for health damage, honor, dignity and property damage;

e) Be information about relevant rights and obligations in the process of resolving conflicts and disputes among family members, handling domestic violence acts;

g) Complaints, denunciations and lawsuits for violations of the law on domestic violence prevention and control;

h) Other rights in accordance with the law related to domestic violence prevention and control.

2. People with domestic violence, guardian or legal representative of people with domestic violence are responsible for providing adequate, accurate and timely information related to domestic violence acts.When required by competent agencies, organizations and individuals.

The responsibility of the person who commits domestic violence

1. People who commit domestic violence are responsible:

a) Ending domestic violence;

b) Observe the requirements and decisions of competent agencies, organizations and individuals when applying, preventing, preventing, protecting, supporting and handling violations of violence against the lawfamily;

c) Timely bring people with domestic violence to emergency or treat.Take care of people with domestic violence, except for cases of domestic violence, guardian or legal representative of a person who is denied by domestic violence;

d) Compensation for damage and overcoming the consequences of themselves causing people with domestic violence, participants in prevention and control of domestic violence and other organizations and individuals.

2. People who commit domestic violence who are guardians or legal representatives of people with domestic violence are not allowed to exercise the rights of the guardian or legal representative prescribed by this Law.For the case of domestic violence.

Purpose, requirements in information, communication, education

1. Information, communication and education on domestic violence prevention and control in order to raise awareness and guide behavior, contribute to the elimination of domestic violence.

2. Information, communication and education on domestic violence prevention and control must ensure the following requirements:

a) Regular, accurate, clear, simple and practical;

b) Suitable for the qualifications, age, gender, tradition, culture, ethnicity, religion and locality;Pay attention to children, pregnant women, women who are raising children under 36 months of age, elderly people, people with disabilities, people who are unable to take care of themselves, people living in ethnic minority areas and regionmountains and areas with difficult socio -economic conditions and areas with extremely difficult socio -economic conditions;

c) Focus on changing the behavior of people who commit domestic violence, who often commit acts of promoting violence, discrimination, discrimination of gender, gender, gender prejudice;

d) Gender equality, protecting the honor, dignity and reputation of people with domestic violence and related people;

d) Ensuring information security about private life, personal secrets and family secrets.

Forms of information, communication, education

Information, communication and education on domestic violence prevention and control are carried out through the following forms:

1. Conference, seminar, training, thematic talk;direct law dissemination;

2. Mass media, loudspeakers, internet, pa-tissue, pressure, and cheerleading paintings;

3. Integrating in programs and operations at educational institutions;

4. Organizing competitions and media campaigns;

5. Integrating in literary, artistic, sports, union activities, community activities;model of domestic violence prevention and control;

6. Other forms in accordance with the provisions of law.

Consulting on domestic violence prevention and control

1. CONTENTS OF CONSULTANCE IN DIRECTOR PREVENTION AND PREVENTION Including:

a) Information, knowledge and laws on prevention and control of domestic violence, marriage and family, gender, gender equality and relevant laws;Rights and responsibilities of people with domestic violence and other family members;

b) Code of behavior in family, organizing family life, building happy families, handling when acts of domestic violence, caring for people with domestic violence.

2. Consulting on domestic violence prevention and control focuses on the following subjects:

a) People with domestic violence;

b) People who commit domestic violence;

c) Children, pregnant women, women are raising children under 36 months of age, elderly people, people with disabilities, people who are unable to take care of themselves;People living in ethnic minority and mountainous areas, areas with difficult socio -economic conditions and areas with extremely difficult socio -economic conditions;

d) People often commit acts of promoting violence, discrimination, gender discrimination, gender, gender prejudice;

d) The person preparing to get married.

3. People's Committees at all levels shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with the Women's Union of the same level and other agencies, organizations and individuals guiding and facilitating consulting activities;fostering knowledge and skills on domestic violence prevention and control for people who perform advice on domestic violence prevention and control at the grassroots level.

Reconciliation in domestic violence prevention and control

1. Mediation in domestic violence prevention and control is the person who conducts mediation guides the parties to voluntarily resolve conflicts and disputes among family members so as not to arise and recur violent acts.family.

Reconciliation in domestic violence prevention and control does not replace measures to handle people who have acts of domestic violence.

2. The conciliation in domestic violence prevention and control must ensure the following principles:

a) Timely, timely and persistent;

b) Respect the voluntary of the parties and the safety of people with domestic violence;

c) Objective, equal, reasonable, affectionate, in accordance with the provisions of the law and the fine traditions of the Vietnamese nation;

d) Ensuring the confidentiality of information about the private life of family members being reconciled;

d) Respect the legitimate rights and interests of others;Do not infringe the interests of the state, public interests.

News and denunciations about domestic violence

1. Address to receive news and denounce domestic violence includes:

a) The People's Committee of the commune where domestic violence occurred;

b) Police agencies and border posts near the place where domestic violence occurred;

c) Educational institutions where people with domestic violence are learners;

d) Village heads, heads of residential groups, heads of Front Task Force in residential areas where domestic violence occurred;

d) The head of the socio -political organization at the commune where domestic violence occurred;

e) National telephone switchboard on domestic violence prevention and control.

2. The report and denunciation of domestic violence acts to the address specified in Clause 1 of this Article comply with the following forms:

a) Calling and texting;

b) Send an application and letter;

c) Directly notify the news.

3. The Government stipulates the national telephone switchboard on domestic violence prevention and control to receive and handle notice and denunciations about domestic violence.

Measures to prevent domestic violence and protect and support people with domestic violence

1. Measures to prevent domestic violence and protection, supporting people with domestic violence include:

a) Forced to end domestic violence;

b) Request those who commit domestic violence to the commune police headquarters where domestic violence occurred;

c) Prohibition of contact;

d) Arranging temporary shelter and supporting essential needs;

d) Care and treat people with domestic violence;

e) Legal assistance and psychological advice and skills to respond to domestic violence;

g) Education and support for conversion of domestic violence;

h) Commenting and criticizing people who commit domestic violence in the community;

i) Carry out the task of serving the community;

k) Measures to prevent and ensure handling of administrative violations in accordance with the law on handling of administrative violations;Measures to prevent and protect the victims in accordance with the law on criminal proceedings for people who commit domestic violence.

2. The application of measures prescribed at Points a, b, c, d, dd, e, g, h and i Clause 1 of this Article for foreigners residing in Vietnam comply with the provisions of the main.coverage.

Education, support for conversion of domestic violence

1. People who commit domestic violence are educated and supported the conversion of domestic violence;Participate in educational services, support the conversion of domestic violence acts provided by domestic violence prevention and control establishments.

2. Content of education, support for conversion of domestic violence include:

a) Policies and laws on domestic violence prevention and control and measures to handle people who commit domestic violence;

b) Identify domestic violence and responsibilities of people who commit domestic violence;

c) Skills to behave, prevent and handle conflicts and disputes in the family;

d) Knowledge and skills to control domestic violence;relieve pressure and stress;

d) Other contents.

3. The President of the People's Committee of the commune decides and organizes the education, supporting the conversion of domestic violence against domestic violence but not to the extent of examination of image liability.The.

Comments and criticism of people who commit domestic violence in the community

1. Measures to comment and criticize people who commit domestic violence in the community are carried out for people aged 18 or older in the following cases:

a) Having acts of domestic violence of twice up or more for 12 months without being sanctioned for administrative violations or applying administrative handling measures;

b) Having acts of domestic violence that has been sanctioned for administrative violations and continues to commit domestic violence.

2. Village heads and heads of the residential group shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with the head of the Front Task Force in the residential area to organize the comments and criticism of people who commit domestic violence in the community.Participants in comments and criticism include:

a) People who commit domestic violence;

b) Family representative;

c) Representative of the commune police;

d) Representatives of the socio -political organization at the commune where people who commit domestic violence or domestic violence are members;

d) Other components invited by the head of the village and the head of the residential group.

3. Content of suggestions and criticism include:

a) Commenting and criticizing people who commit domestic violence;

b) Provide the provisions of the law on domestic violence prevention and control;

c) Request those who commit domestic violence against domestic violence.

4. Presidents of the People's Committee of the commune where people commit domestic violence to decide and organize the implementation of measures to comment and criticize people who commit domestic violence in the community.The proposal of the person assigned to handle domestic violence acts.

5. The People's Committee of the commune where people committing domestic violence are responsible for creating favorable conditions for the head of the village and the head of the residential group to organize the comments and criticisms of people who commit domestic violence actsIn the community.

6. In case the person who commits domestic violence acts specified in Clause 1 of this Article voluntarily performs the task of serving the community prescribed in Article 33 of this Law, the comments and criticisms are not applied in the plus.Dong resident.

Domestic violence prevention and control facility

1. Domestic violence prevention and control facilities carry out the care, advice, arrange temporary places, support the essential needs of people with domestic violence and children whom people with violence.communal house is responsible for caring and nurturing;Education, support for conversion of domestic violence.

2. Domestic violence prevention and control facilities include:

a) Reliable address;

b) Medical examination and treatment establishments;

c) Social assistance facilities;

d) The State legal aid center, organized legal aid;

d) Other establishments participate in domestic violence prevention and control;

e) Facility providing domestic violence prevention and control services.

Facility provides domestic violence prevention and control services

1. Facilities providing domestic violence prevention and control services established by agencies, organizations and individuals in accordance with the law, operating without profit purposes to provide one or some.The following service and operation:

a) Advice on domestic violence prevention and control;

b) Temporarily shun and other essential needs for people with domestic violence;

c) Education and support for conversion of domestic violence;

d) Health care and prevention of mental illness for people with domestic violence;

d) Other activities related to domestic violence prevention and control.

2. The basis specified in Clause 1 of this Article must meet the following conditions:

a) The head of the facility has full civil act capacity, with a university degree or higher, the training is related to the registration service to participate in the supply, not yet examined for penal liability.or have not been handled administrative violations on domestic violence;

b) Employees who directly participate in providing support services for domestic violence prevention and control must graduate from high school or higher, have been fostered with knowledge and skills on domestic violence prevention and control due to muscle.The state officials are competent to organize or establishments that are authorized by competent state agencies;

c) In case the establishment provides temporary shelter for people with domestic violence or providing educational services, supporting the conversion of behavior, which must have facilities and places to ensure the requirements.

3. The basis specified in Clause 1 of this Article register the contents and scope of activities with the state management agency on domestic violence prevention and control.

4. Organizations and individuals investing in funding, human resources and facilities to perform services and activities specified in Clause 1 of this Article shall be subject to tax, fees, credit and other incentives as prescribedunder the law.

5. The Government details Clause 2 of this Article;Regulate the authority, order and procedures for granting and revoking the establishment registration certificate of the provider of domestic violence prevention and control services.

