Responsibilities of ministries, ministerial -level agencies, government -attached agencies

1. The Ministry of Health has the following responsibility:

a) Promulgating and organizing the implementation of regulations on care and treatment for patients who are people with domestic violence at medical examination and treatment establishments;

b) To guide medical examination and treatment establishments to implement statistics and report cases where patients are people with domestic violence;

c) Fostering knowledge and skills for medical staff to conduct consultancy, care and treatment of domestic violence.

2. The Ministry of Labor, War Invalids and Social Affairs has the following responsibility:

a) Promulgate according to its competence or submit to competent state agencies to promulgate legal documents on social aid establishments;guide the receipt and assistance of domestic violence at social assistance facilities;

b) Direct the integration of domestic violence prevention and control into the program and plan on gender equality, protecting children, the elderly, people with disabilities, vocational education, job creation,reduce poverty and prevent and combat social evils;

c) Guide social assistance facilities to carry out statistics and report cases of domestic violence being received and assisted at social aid facilities.

3. The Ministry of Education and Training has the following responsibility:

a) Direct the integration of domestic violence prevention and control knowledge into the education and training program in accordance with the requirements of each field of study and education;

b) Guide educational institutions to receive, detect and support learners with domestic violence.

4. The following Ministry of Information and Communications is responsible:

a) Direct the mass media agencies informing and propagating policies and laws on domestic violence prevention and control;

b) Assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with relevant agencies to detect and prevent information, images, data on cyberspace, in the press, in video games and publishing publications toincite domestic violence.

5. The Ministry of Justice has the following responsibility:

a) Coordinate the dissemination and education of laws on domestic violence prevention and control, fostering knowledge and skills for mediators and legal aids on domestic violence prevention and control;

b) Guide the State Legal Aid Center, organize the legal aid to make statistical reports in case people with domestic violence are legal assistance in accordance with the law on legal assistancephysical.

6. The Ministry of Public Security has the following responsibility:

a) To promulgate documents guiding the supervision of the implementation of the decision to ban contact;

b) Direct the integration of domestic violence prevention and control knowledge into training and retraining programs in educational institutions under their management;

c) To assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate in fostering knowledge and skills for the People's Public Security Forces to conduct domestic violence prevention and control;

d) Guide the implementation of statistics on domestic violence prevention and control under the management responsibility.

7. Ministry, ministerial -level agencies, government -attached agencies, within the scope of their duties and powers, presiding over and coordinating with relevant agencies and organizations to propagate and educate policies,The law on domestic violence prevention and control.

