The exercise of citizens' freedom of residence

1. Citizens exercising the freedom of residence in accordance with this Law and other provisions of relevant laws.

2. The exercise of citizens' freedom of residence is only limited in the following cases:

a) Persons who are carried out by the authorities and persons who are subject to prohibited measures from leaving their residence and detention measures;The person sentenced to imprisonment but has not had a judgment execution decision or has made a judgment execution decision but is on bail or has been postponed the execution of the sentence, suspending the judgment execution;Prison sentenced people are entitled to suspended sentences during the challenge;people who are serving sentences for imprisonment, prohibited residence, probation or non -custodial reform;people who are released from prison ahead of time are in the time of challenges;

b) People who are serving educational measures in communes, wards and townships, measures to be taken to compulsory educational institutions, put into compulsory detoxification establishments and put them into reformatory schools;people must abide by measures to be taken to compulsory educational institutions, put into compulsory detoxification establishments, taken to reformatory but are being postponed or temporarily suspended from observance;The manager during the time of examining and deciding on the application of measures to put into compulsory educational institutions, put into compulsory detoxification establishments, and put them into reformatory schools;

c) People are isolated from the risk of spreading disease to the community;

d) Locations and areas of isolation due to disease prevention and control according to decisions of competent agencies and people;areas with emergency conditions in accordance with law;The location is not allowed to register for new permanent residence, new temporary residence registration, separation of households in accordance with this Law;

d) Other cases as prescribed by the Law.

3. The exercise of the freedom of residence of citizens is only limited in accordance with the law.Content and time to restrict the freedom of residence shall comply with the legally effective judgments and decisions of the Court, the decision of other state agencies competent or in accordance with the relevant law.

Permanent registration conditions

1. Citizens who have a legal accommodation under their ownership shall be registered for permanent residence.

2. Citizens who are registered for permanent residents are not owned by their ownership when the head of the head of the household and the owner of that legal accommodation agrees in the following cases:

a) The wife comes back with her husband;Husband to stay with his wife;I live with my father and mother;father and mother to stay with children;

b) Elderly people who live with their siblings, siblings, siblings, nephews;People with disabilities are particularly serious, people with severe disabilities, people who are unable to work, people with mental illness or other illnesses lose their perceptions, their ability to control behavior with grandfather, grandmother, grandmother,Grandfather, grandmother, brother, sister, younger brother, uncle, uncle, uncle, uncle, aunt, aunt, nephew, guardian;

c) The minor was agreed to be agreed by the father, mother or guardian or no father or mother to stay with the grandmother, the grandmother, the grandfather, the grandmother, the grandmother, the grandmother, the biological brother, the older sister, the younger brotherThe intestines, uncle, uncle, uncle, aunt, aunt;The minor stays with the guardian.

3. Except for the case specified in Clause 2 of this Article, citizens are allowed to register permanent residences legal accommodation by renting, borrowing or staying when meeting the following conditions:

a) Legal accommodation owner agreed to register permanent residence at the lease, borrowing, staying and being agreed by the head of the household if the permanent residence is registered with that household;

b) Ensuring the minimum conditions of housing area prescribed by the provincial People's Council but not less than 08 m2 of floor/person.

4. Citizens who are registered for permanent residence at religious establishments, religious facilities with auxiliary works are houses when one of the following cases:

a) Religious activists are ordained, appointed, elected, elected, and transferred to religious activities at religious establishments;

b) Representative of beliefs;

c) The person who is agreed by the representative or the belief management board for permanent residence registration to directly manage and organize religious activities at the belief establishment;

d) Children, people with especially heavy disabilities, people with heavy disabilities, helpless people rely on the representative or management board of beliefs, heads or representatives of religious facilities to agree to postpermanent residence.

5. Persons who are cared for, nurtured and assisted with permanent residence at the social aid when the head of the facility agreed or was registered for permanent residence in households taking care and nurturing.When the head of the household and the owner of the accommodation legally agreed.

6. Persons living, working working on vehicles are registered permanently at that means when meeting the following conditions:

a) As the owner of the vehicle or the owner of that vehicle agreed to register permanent residence;

b) The vehicle is registered and registered in accordance with the law;In case the vehicle is not subject to registration or registration, there must be certification of the People's Committee of the commune where the vehicle regularly passes and passes on the use of that vehicle for the purpose to stay;

c) There is a confirmation of the People's Committee of the commune about the vehicle that has been registered and passed regularly in the area in case the vehicle does not have to register or the vehicle registration place does not coincide with the place of regular parking,Do.

7. The registration of permanent residence of a minor must have the consent of a father, mother or guardian, unless the residence of the minor is decided by the Court.

8. Citizens must not register new permanent residents at the prescribed in Article 23 of this Law, unless the case specified at Point a, Clause 2 of this Article.

