Delete permanent residence

1. People in one of the following cases are deleted with permanent residence registration:

a) Death;There is a decision of the Court declaring missing or dead;

b) Going abroad to settle down;

c) There has been a decision to cancel permanent registration prescribed in Article 35 of this Law;

d) Continuous absence at a permanent residence for 12 months or more without registering temporary residence or not declaring temporary absence, except in the case of exit abroad but not for settlement or case of beingcomplying with imprisonment sentences, serving measures to put into compulsory educational institutions, put into compulsory detoxification establishments, and taken to reformatory schools;

d) Has been authorized by the competent authority of Vietnam, deprived of Vietnamese nationality, cancel the decision for Vietnamese nationalization;

e) Persons who have registered permanent residence in accommodation due to renting, borrowing, staying but terminating the rent, borrowing, staying, but after 12 months from the date of termination of rental, borrowing, residentresiding in the new place, except for the case specified at P, of this Clause;

g) The person who has registered permanent residence is legal, but then the ownership of the place has been transferred to others, but after 12 months from the date of transfer of ownership has not yet registered permanent residence in the new place, exceptIn case the new owner agrees to continue leasing, lending, lending and lying and registration of permanent residence in the place there or the case specified at H, this Clause;

h) Persons who have registered permanent residence due to renting, borrowing, staying but ending the hire, borrowing, staying and not being leased, loaned, laid by the rental for permanent residence registrationat the place there;The person who has registered a permanent residence is his own ownership but has transferred the ownership of accommodation to others and is not allowed to agree to keep the permanent residence registration there;

i) Persons who have registered permanent residents are demolished and confiscated under a decision of competent state agencies or in vehicles that have been deleted vehicles in accordance with law.

2. Agency has been registered for permanent residence competent to delete permanent residence registration and must specify the reason and time of deletion of permanent residence registration in a database on residence.

3. The Government details the dossiers and procedures for deleting permanent residence registration.

