Struggle to protect network security

1. The struggle to protect network security is an organized activity implemented by a specialized force for cybersecurity on cyberspace to protect national security and ensure social order and safety.

2. Contents of the struggle to protect network security include:

a) Organizing the grasp of the situation related to national security protection activities;

b) Prevention and control of attacks and stable activities of important information systems on national security;

c) Paralys or limit cyber spatial use in order to cause national security harm or cause particularly serious damage to social order and safety;

d) Actively attack disabling goals on cyberspace to protect national security and ensure social order and safety.

3. The Ministry of Public Security shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with the concerned ministries and branches to struggle to protect network security.

Deploying activities to protect cybersecurity in state agencies and political organizations at the central and local levels

1. Contents of implementing network security protection activities include:

a) Develop and complete regulations and regulations on using internal computer networks, computer networks with internet connection;plan to ensure network security for the information system;plans to respond and overcome network security incidents;

b) Application and implementation of plans, measures and technologies to protect cybersecurity for information and information systems, documents stored, drafted and transmitted on information systems within the scope ofphysical;

c) Organizing fostering knowledge of cybersecurity for cadres, civil servants, officials and employees;improve network security protection for network security forces;

d) Protect cybersecurity in providing public services on cyberspace, providing, exchanging, collecting information with agencies, organizations, individuals, sharing internal information and with the opportunityother officials or in other activities as prescribed by the Government;

d) Investing and building facilities in accordance with conditions to ensure the implementation of network security protection activities for the information system;

e) Checking network security for the information system;prevention and control of violations of the law on cybersecurity;respond and overcome network security incidents.

2. The heads of agencies and organizations shall have to implement cybersecurity protection activities under their management.

Research and development of cybersecurity

1. Content of research and development of network security includes:

a) Building software systems, network security equipment;

b) Methods of software evaluation, network security protection equipment meets the standards and limits the existence of weaknesses, security holes, malware;

c) Methods of hardware and software testing are provided with the function;

d) Methods of protecting state secrets, working secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life;security ability when transmitting information on cyberspace;

d) Determining the origin of the information transmitted on cyberspace;

e) Solve the risk of cyber security threat;

g) Building network sports, network security testing environment;

h) Technical initiatives to raise awareness and skills on network security;

i) Forecast of network security;

k) Practical research, developing cybersecurity theory.

2. Relevant agencies, organizations and individuals have the right to research and develop cybersecurity.

Improve cybersecurity capacity

1. The State encourages and creates favorable conditions for agencies, organizations and individuals to improve their ability to autonomy in cybersecurity and improve the ability to produce, inspect, evaluate and test digital equipment and translationNetwork crop, network application.

2. The Government implements the following measures to improve the capacity of cybersecurity for agencies, organizations and individuals:

a) Promote the transfer, research, master and develop technology, products, services and applications to protect network security;

b) Promote the application of new technology and advanced technology related to cybersecurity;

c) Organize training, development and use of cybersecurity human resources;

d) Strengthen the business environment, improve competitive conditions to support businesses to research and produce products, services and applications to protect network security.

Responsibility of the Ministry of Public Security

The Ministry of Public Security is responsible to the Government to perform the state management of cybersecurity and have the following duties and powers, except for the content of the Ministry of Defense and the Government Cipher Committee:

1. To promulgate or submit to competent state agencies to promulgate and guide the implementation of legal documents on cybersecurity;

2. Develop and propose strategies, guidelines, policies, plans and plans to protect network security;

3. Preventing and struggling with cyber spaces violating sovereignty, interests, national security, social order and safety and cybercrime prevention;

4. Ensuring information security on cyberspace;Develop a mechanism to authenticate the number of account registration information;Warning, sharing network security information, risk of cyber security threats;

5. To advise and propose the Government and the Prime Minister to consider and decide the assignment and coordination of the implementation of network security protection measures, prevention and handling of cybersecurity violations in the school.convergence of state management related to the scope of management of many ministries and branches;

6. Organizing drills to prevent and combat cyber attacks;rehearsal response and troubleshooting of network security incidents for important information systems on national security;

7. Checking, inspecting and settling complaints, denunciations and handling violations of cybersecurity laws.

Responsibility of the Ministry of Defense

The Ministry of Defense is responsible to the Government to perform state management of cyber security within the management scope and have the following tasks and powers:

1. To promulgate or submit to the competent state agency to promulgate and guide the implementation of legal documents on cyber security within the scope of management;

2. Develop and propose strategies, guidelines, policies, plans and plans to protect network security within the management scope;

3. Preventing and struggling with cyberspace activities that violate national security within the management scope;

4. Coordinating with the Ministry of Public Security to organize drills to prevent and combat cyber attacks, response drills, troubleshooting network security incidents for important information systems on national security and public implementationnetwork security protection;

5. Checking, inspecting, settling complaints, denunciations and handling violations of cybersecurity laws within the scope of management.

The responsibility of the service provider in cyberspace

1. Enterprises providing services on cyberspace in Vietnam are responsible for the following:

a) Warning the possibility of insecurity in the use of services on the cyberspace provided and guided to prevent preventive measures;

b) Develop plans and solutions to respond quickly to cybersecurity incidents, immediately handle weaknesses, security holes, malware, cyber attacks, network intrusion and other security risks;When a network security incident occurred, immediately implemented an emergency plan, appropriate response measures, and reported to a specialized force to protect network security in accordance with this Law;

c) Applying technical solutions and other necessary measures to ensure the security of information collection, preventing the risk of revealing, leaking, damaging or losing data;In case of occurrence or a risk of incidents of revealing, falling, damaging or losing data of users, it is necessary to immediately offer solutions to respond, and notify the user and report it tospecialized forces to protect network security in accordance with this Law;

d) Coordinate and create conditions for specialized forces to protect network security in network security protection.

2. Enterprises providing services on telecommunications networks, internet, and increasing services on cyberspace in Vietnam are responsible for implementing the provisions of Clause 1 of this Article, Clause 2 and Clause 3, Article 26 of the LawThis.

The National Assembly has the following tasks and powers:

1. To make the Constitution and amend the Constitution;make laws and amend laws;

2. Implementing the Supreme Supervisory Right to comply with the Constitution, Law and Resolution of the National Assembly;Considering the work report of the President, the National Assembly Standing Committee, the Government, the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's Procuracy, the National Election Council, the State Audit and other agenciesestablished by the National Assembly;

3. To decide the objectives, targets, policies and basic tasks of socio -economic development of the country;

4. Basic policy decisions on national finance and monetary;regulations, amendments or abolition of taxes;decide to divide revenues and spending tasks between the central budget and the local budget;decide on national debt safety limits, public debt, and government debt;decide on the state budget estimate and allocate central budgets, approve the state budget settlement;

5. Decision on ethnic policies and religious policies of the State;

6. Regulations on organization and operation of the National Assembly, the President, the Government, the People's Court, the People's Procuracy, the National Election Council, the State Audit, the local government and the agency and the agencyOther established by the National Assembly;

7. Election, dismissal, dismissal of the State, Vice President, Chairman of the National Assembly, Vice Chairman of the National Assembly, Member of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly, Chairman of the Ethnic Council, Chairman of the CommitteeThe National Assembly, the Prime Minister, the Chief Justice of the Supreme People's Court, the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy, the Chairman of the National Election Council, the State Auditor General, the head of another agency by the NationalEstablished Association;approving the proposal for appointment, dismissal and dismissal of Deputy Prime Ministers, Ministers and other members of the Government, Judges of the Supreme People's Court;Approve the list of members of the National Defense and Security Council, the National Election Council.

After being elected, the President, the President of the National Assembly, the Prime Minister, the Chief Justice of the Supreme People's Court must swear loyalty to the Fatherland, the People and the Constitution;

8. Vote for confidence for the person holding a position elected or approved by the National Assembly;

9. Decision on establishment, abolition of ministries and ministerial -level agencies of the Government;establishing, dissolving, entering, dividing and adjusting administrative boundaries of provinces and cities directly under the Central Government, special administrative and economic unit;establishing and abolishing other agencies in accordance with the Constitution and Law;

10. To abolish documents of the President, the Standing Committee of the National Assembly, the Government, the Prime Minister, the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's Procuracy contrary to the Constitution, Law, Resolution ofCongress;

11. Decision of great amnesty;

12. Regulating functions and levels in the people's armed forces, functions, diplomatic levels and other state functions and levels;regulating medals, medals and titles of the State honor;

13. Decision on war and peace;regulations on emergency status, other special measures to ensure national defense and security;

14. Basic policy decision on foreign affairs;ratify, decide to join or terminate the effectiveness of international treaties related to war, peace, national sovereignty, members of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam at international organizations.And important areas, international treaties on human rights, basic rights and obligations of citizens and other international treaties contrary to the laws and resolutions of the National Assembly;

15. Decision on referendum.

The Standing Committee of the National Assembly has the following tasks and powers:

1. Organizing the preparation, summoning and chairing the National Assembly meeting;

2. Ordinance on issues assigned by the National Assembly;explain the constitution, laws and ordinances;

3. Supervising the implementation of the Constitution, Law, Resolution of the National Assembly, Ordinance and Resolutions of the National Assembly Standing Committee;supervise the activities of the Government, the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's Procuracy, the State Audit and other agencies established by the National Assembly;

4. Suspend the implementation of documents of the Government, the Prime Minister, the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's Procuracy contrary to the Constitution, laws, resolutions of the National Assembly and submit to the National Assembly for decisionThe abolition of that document at the nearest meeting;abolish documents of the Government, the Prime Minister, the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's Procuracy contrary to the Ordinance and Resolution of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly;

5. Directing, regulating and coordinating the activities of the National Council and Committees of the National Assembly;guide and ensure the operating conditions of the National Assembly deputies;

6. Proposing the National Assembly to elect, dismiss and dismiss the President, Chairman of the National Assembly, Vice Chairman of the National Assembly, Member of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly, Chairman of the Ethnic Council, Chairman of the National CommitteeAssociation, Chairman of National Election Council, State Auditor General;

7. Monitoring and guiding the activities of the People's Council;abolish the resolutions of the People's Council of provinces and centrally -run cities contrary to the Constitution, laws and documents of superior state agencies;disbanding the People's Councils of provinces and cities directly under the Central Government in case the People's Council seriously damages the interests of the people;

8. The decision to establish, dissolve, enter, divide and adjust the boundaries of administrative units under the province or city directly under the Central Government;

9. Deciding on the declaration of war in case the National Assembly cannot meet and report to the National Assembly to decide at the nearest session;

10. Decision on general encouragement or local encouragement;Proposing, abolishing emergency in the country or in each locality;

11. Implementing the foreign relations of the National Assembly;

12. Approving the proposal to appoint and dismiss the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam;

13. Organize a referendum according to the decision of the National Assembly.

The President has the following tasks and powers:

1. Announcing the constitution, laws and ordinances;Proposing the Standing Committee of the National Assembly to revise the Ordinance within ten days from the date the Ordinance is approved, if the Ordinance is still approved by the National Assembly Standing Committee, but the President still does notagreed, the President submitted to the National Assembly to decide at the latest meeting;

2. Proposing the National Assembly to elect, dismiss and dismiss the Vice President and the Prime Minister;Based on the Resolution of the National Assembly, appointing, dismissing and dismissing the Deputy Prime Minister, Minister and other members of the Government;

3. Proposing the National Assembly to elect, dismiss and dismiss the Chief Justice of the Supreme People's Court, the Head of the Supreme People's Procuracy;Based on the Resolution of the National Assembly, appointing, dismissing and dismissing judges of the Supreme People's Court;appointing, dismissing and dismissing Deputy Chief Justice of the Supreme People's Court, Judges of other courts, Deputy Directors and Procurators of the Supreme People's Procuracy;Special amnesty decision;Based on the Resolution of the National Assembly, announcing the decision of the Great Xa;

4. Decision on awarding medals, medals, state awards, the title of State honor;decide for naturalization, citizenship, returning to nationality or deprivation of Vietnamese nationality;

5. dominate the people's armed forces, hold the Chairman of the Council of Defense and Security;decide to Phong, Thang, Christmas, deprive the rank of general, the Admiral, the Vice Admiral, the Admiral of the Navy;appointing, dismissing and dismissing the Chief of the General Staff, Chairman of the General Department of Politics of the Vietnam People's Army;Based on the Resolution of the National Assembly or the Standing Committee of the National Assembly, announcing and abolishing the decision to declare the status of war;Based on the Resolution of the Standing Committee of the National Assembly, ordering the general encouragement or local encouragement, announcing and abolishing the emergency situation;In case the National Assembly Standing Committee cannot meet, announce and abolish emergency in the country or in each locality;

6. Receiving the Ambassador Extraordinary and Extentionion of Foreign Countries;Pursuant to the Resolution of the National Assembly Standing Committee, appoint and dismiss;The decision to appoint and summon Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam;Phong Ham and Ambassador;decision to negotiate and sign international treaties on the name of the State;submit to the National Assembly approving and deciding to join or terminate the international treaty prescribed in Clause 14, Article 70;The decision to approve, join or terminate other international treaties on the name of the State.

