Conditions for recognition of tourist area
1. Conditions for recognition of provincial tourist area include:

a) Having tourism resources with the advantage of natural landscapes or cultural values, with defined boundaries;

b) Having infrastructure, technical facilities, services to meet the needs of accommodation, eating and other needs of tourists;

c) There is a connection with the national transport and telecommunications infrastructure system;

d) Meeting conditions for security, social order and safety, environmental protection in accordance with the law.

2. Conditions for recognition of national tourist area include:

a) Having a variety of tourism resources, especially attractive with the advantage of natural landscapes or cultural values, with defined boundaries;

b) Having in the list of potential areas for development of national tourist area approved by competent state agencies;

c) Having infrastructure, technical facilities, high quality and synchronous services, meeting the needs of accommodation, eating and other needs of tourists;

d) The conditions specified at Points c and d, Clause 1 of this Article.

3. The Government details this.

Dossiers, order, procedures and authority to recognize the provincial tourist area
1. The application for recognition of the provincial tourist area includes:

a) Application for recognition of the provincial tourism area according to the form set by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) The explanation of the conditions for recognizing the provincial tourist area prescribed in Clause 1, Article 26 of this Law.

2. The order, procedures and authority to recognize the provincial tourist area are stipulated as follows:

a) District -level People's Committees or organization of tourist areas shall submit 01 set of dossiers to the provincial tourism specialized agencies where the tourist area;

b) Within 45 days from the date of receipt of a valid dossier, the provincial -level specialized agency appraised and submitted to the provincial People's Committee;

c) Within 15 days from the date of receiving the evaluation results, the provincial People's Committee decides to recognize the provincial tourist area;In case of refusal, must reply in writing and specify the reason.

3. For resorts located in the area of ‚Äã‚Äã02 administrative units at district or higher, the provincial tourism specialized agencies shall make a dossier of request for recognition of the provincial tourist area.The provincial People's Committee established the appraisal council, decided to recognize the provincial tourist area.

4. The provincial People's Committee revokes the decision to recognize the provincial -level tourist area in case the resort no longer meets the conditions specified in Clause 1, Article 26 of this Law.

Records, order, procedures and authority to recognize the national tourist area
1. The application for recognition of the national tourist area includes:

a) Application for recognition of national tourist area according to the form set by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) The explanation of the conditions for recognizing the national tourist area prescribed in Clause 2, Article 26 of this Law.

2. The order, procedures and authority to recognize the national tourist area are prescribed as follows:

a) The provincial People's Committee shall submit 01 set of dossiers to the Vietnam National Administration of Tourism;

b) Within 45 days from the date of receipt of a valid dossier, the Vietnam National Administration of Tourism evaluate and submit to the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

c) Within 15 days from the date of receiving the evaluation results, the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism decided to recognize and coordinate with the provincial People's Committee to organize the announcement of the tourist area.family;In case of refusal, must reply in writing and specify the reason.

3. For resorts located in the area of ‚Äã‚Äã02 administrative units at the provincial level or higher, the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism shall make a dossier of request for recognition of the National Tourism Area to submit to the Prime Minister for recognition.

4. Persons competent to recognize the national tourist area revoke the decision to recognize in case the tourist area no longer meets the conditions specified in Clause 2, Article 26 of this Law.

Tourist area management

1. Content of tourist area management includes:

a) Manage the planning and development investment;

b) Manage tourism service business activities, activities of tour guides;

c) Manage the investment, exploitation and protection of tourism resources;

d) Ensuring safety for tourists;ensure social order and safety, protect the environment in the tourist area;

d) Building a system of signs, instruction signs, and providing information points for tourists;

e) Other contents as prescribed by law.

2. The Government stipulates the model of national tourist area management;The provincial People's Committee stipulates the management model of the provincial tourist area.

Conditions for business travel services
1. Conditions for domestic travel services include:

a) As an enterprise established in accordance with the law on enterprises;

b) Deposit of domestic travel services at the bank;

c) The person in charge of the travel service business must graduate from intermediate or higher in travel majoring;In case of high school or higher degree in other specialties, there must be a certificate of domestic tourism management.

2. Conditions for international travel services include:

a) As an enterprise established in accordance with the law on enterprises;

b) Deposit of international travel service business at the bank;

c) The person in charge of the travel service business must graduate from college or higher in travel;In case of graduating from a college or higher, other specialized specialty must have a certificate of international tourism management.

3. Enterprises meeting the business conditions specified in Clause 1 of this Article shall be granted a domestic travel service business license;Meeting the business conditions specified in Clause 2 of this Article is granted an international travel service business license.

The appraisal fee for granting international travel service business licenses, domestic travel service business licenses shall comply with the law on fees and fees.

4. The Government details the deposit of the travel service business specified at Point b, Clause 1 and Point b, Clause 2 of this Article.

5. The Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism details detailing the person in charge of the travel service business;Content of training, retraining, organizing exams and certificates of domestic tourism operations and international tourism operations.

Dossiers, order, procedures, authority to grant domestic travel business licenses
1. The application for a domestic travel service business license includes:

a) Application for granting domestic travel business licenses according to the form set by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Certified copies of enterprise registration certificates;

c) Certificate of travel business service deposit;

d) Certified copies of appointment decisions or labor contracts between travel services and travel services and travel services;

d) Certified copy of certification of diplomas and certificates of the person in charge of the travel service business prescribed at Point c, Clause 1, Article 31 of this Law.

2. The order, procedures and authority for granting domestic travel services are prescribed as follows:

a) The enterprise proposes to issue a domestic travel service business license submit 01 set of dossiers to the provincial tourism specialized agency where the enterprise is headquartered;

b) Within 10 days from the date of receipt of a valid dossier, the provincial -level specialized agency evaluates and granting a domestic travel business license for enterprises;In case of refusal, it is necessary to notify in writing and specify the reason.

3. The Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism stipulates the model of domestic travel service business license.

Profile, order, procedures, competence to grant international travel business licenses
1. The application for an international travel service business license includes:

a) Application for granting international travel service licenses according to the form set by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Certified copies of enterprise registration certificates or investment registration certificates issued by competent state agencies;

c) Certificate of travel business service deposit;

d) Certified copy of diplomas and certificates of the travel service business person specified at Point c, Clause 2, Article 31 of this Law;

d) Certified copy of appointment decisions or labor contracts between travel services and travel services in charge of travel services.

2. The order, procedures and authority for granting international travel services are prescribed as follows:

a) The enterprise proposes to issue an international travel service business license submit 01 dossier to the Vietnam National Administration of Tourism;

b) Within 10 days from the date of receipt of a valid dossier, the Vietnam National Administration of Tourism appraises, granted an international travel service business license for the business and notifies the tourism specialized agency.The province where the business is headquartered;In case of refusal, it is necessary to notify in writing and specify the reason.

3. The Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism stipulates the international travel service business license form.

Granting of travel business licenses
1. The enterprise proposes to change the travel business license in the following cases:

a) Change the business registration certificate or investment registration certificate;

b) Change the scope of international travel services.

2. Dossiers of request for exchange of travel business licenses include:

a) Application for renewal of travel business licenses according to the form prescribed by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) The business license of the enterprise;

c) Certified copies of enterprise registration certificates or investment registration certificates in the case specified at Point a, Clause 1 of this Article;Certificate of travel business service deposit in accordance with the scope of business in the case specified at Point b, Clause 1 of this Article.

3. The order and procedures for granting business licenses are prescribed as follows:

a) Enterprises submit 01 set of dossiers to competent state agencies that have granted licenses;

b) Within 05 working days from the date of receipt of a valid dossier, the competent state agency granted a license shall grant a change of travel business license for enterprises;In case of refusal, it is necessary to notify in writing and specify the reason.

The Vietnam National Administration of Tourism informs the provincial tourism specialized agencies where the enterprise is headquartered when the exchange of international travel service business license.

Review business license for travel services
1. Enterprises whose license is revoked the travel service business license in the following cases:

a) Termination of travel, dissolution or bankruptcy services;

b) Do not meet one of the conditions for business service business specified in Clause 1 or Clause 2, Article 31 of this Law;

c) Failing to change the travel service business license as prescribed in Clause 1, Article 35 of this Law;

d) Make harms to sovereignty, national interests, national defense and security;

d) Taking advantage of tourism activities to bring people from Vietnam to foreign countries or from abroad to Vietnam illegally;

e) For other organizations and individuals to use the business license business license of the enterprise to operate in business;

g) Failure to fulfill the obligations specified at Point i, Clause 1, Article 37 of this Law, causing serious damage to the life, health and property of tourists;

h) Forging dossiers of request for granting, renewing and re -granting business licenses.

2. The enterprise has been revoked the travel service business license as prescribed at Points b and c, Clause 1 of this Article will only be requested to issue a travel service business license after 06 months from the date of decision.Review the validity of the license.The enterprise has been revoked the travel service business license as prescribed at the points d, dd, e, g and h, Clause 1 of this Article will only be proposed to issue a travel business license after 12 months of tellingFrom the date of decision to revoke the validity of the license.

3. The Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism stipulates the order and procedures for revoking the travel business license.

Rights and obligations of travel services
1. The following local travel service business has the following rights and obligations:

a) Develop, advertise, sell and organize the implementation of tourism services and tourism programs for tourists according to the scope of business prescribed in the license;

b) Ensuring the maintenance of travel services as prescribed in Clause 1, Article 31 of this Law;publicize the name of the enterprise, the number of travel services on the signboard at the headquarters, branches, transaction offices, in travel contracts, on advertising publications and in electronic transactions;

c) Notice of changing the person in charge of travel service business, sending records to the person in charge of the travel service business instead of the competent state agency to issue a license within 15 days of narrationFrom the change;

d) Provide information about programs, services, tourist destinations for tourists;

d) Buy insurance for tourists during the implementation of the tourism program, except for cases where tourists have had insurance for the entire tourism program;

e) Use tour guides to guide tourists under travel contracts;take responsibility for the operation of tour guides during the time to guide tourists under the contract;

g) Observe, disseminate and guide tourists to comply with the laws and regulations of the tourist destination;Civilized behavior, respect for cultural identities, customs and practices of Vietnam and tourism destinations;coordinate with competent state agencies to promptly handle violations of laws of tourists while participating in the tourism program;

h) Implementing the regime of reporting, statistics, accounting and storing records in accordance with the law;

i) Apply measures to ensure the safety of life, health and property of tourists;promptly notify the competent state agency about accidents and risks that occur with tourists and take measures to overcome consequences;

k) Managing tourists under the tourism program agreed with tourists.

2. International travel service businesses serving international tourists coming to Vietnam have the following rights and obligations:

a) Rights and obligations specified at points a, c, d, dd, e, g, h, i and k, Clause 1 of this Article;

b) Ensuring the maintenance of travel services as prescribed in Clause 2, Article 31 of this Law;publicize the name of the enterprise, the number of travel services on the signboard at the headquarters, branches, transaction offices, in travel contracts, on advertising publications and in electronic transactions;

c) Support tourists to carry out entry procedures, exit, transit and customs.

3. International travel service businesses to serve tourists abroad have the following rights and obligations:

a) Rights and obligations specified at Points a, c, d, dd, g, h, i and k, Clause 1, Point b and Point c, Clause 2 of this Article;

b) Use international tour guide to take tourists abroad under travel contracts;Responsible for the operation of tour guides during the time to take tourists abroad.

Travel contract

1. The travel contract is an agreement on the implementation of the tourism program between the travel service business with businesses, tourists or representatives of tourists.

2. The travel contract must be made in writing.

3. The travel contract must have the following contents:

a) Clearly describing the quantity, quality, service price, time and way of providing services in the tourism program;

b) Contract value and payment method;

c) Terms of exclusion of liability in case of force majeure;

d) Financial conditions and responsibilities related to the change, addition and cancellation of the contract;

d) Terms of insurance for tourists.

Travel agent contract
1. The travel agent contract must be made in writing between the agent assignee who is a travel service business and the agent is an organization or individual business.

2. The travel agent contract must have the following contents:

a) Name and address of the agent and agent assignee;

b) Tourism programs, tourism program prices are delivered to agents, agent commissions, payment time;

c) Rights and responsibilities of the parties;

d) The validity period of the agent contract.

Tourist accommodation business conditions
1. Conditions for business accommodation services include:
a) There is a business registration in accordance with the law;

b) Meeting conditions for security, order and safety on fire prevention and fighting, environmental protection and food safety as prescribed by law;

c) Meet the minimum conditions for technical facilities and services for tourists.

2. The Government details Point c, Clause 1 of this Article.

Rights and obligations of organizations and individuals business tourist accommodation services
1. Organizations and individuals business tourist accommodation services have the following right:

a) Refuse to receive tourists who violate the law, violate the rules of tourist accommodation establishments or when the tourist accommodation establishment is no longer able to meet the requirements of tourists;

b) Cancellation of service provision contracts for tourists who violate the law and violate the rules of tourist accommodation establishments.

2. Organizations and individuals business tourist accommodation services have the following obligations:

a) Ensuring the maintenance of tourist accommodation services as prescribed in Clause 1, Article 49 of this Law;

b) Publicly posting the price of goods and services and rules of tourist accommodation establishments;

c) Compensation for damage to tourists in accordance with civil law;

d) Notice in writing to the provincial tourism specialized agencies where there is a tourist accommodation establishment when there is a change in the name of the establishment, scale, address and legal representative;

d) Only use the word "star" or star image to advertise the tourist accommodation establishment after being recognized by a competent state agency;

e) Implement the regime of reporting, statistics and accounting in accordance with the law.

3. Organizations and individuals business tourist accommodation services have been recognized as the following rights and obligations:

a) Rights and obligations specified in Clauses 1 and 2 of this Article;

b) Hanging signs to recognize tourist accommodation and advertising establishments with the type and class that has been recognized;

c) Maintain the quality of tourist accommodation establishments according to the type and class that has been recognized.

Developing other types of travel services
The State encourages organizations and individuals to carry out the following activities:

1. Investing and building dining restaurants, food and culinary areas in order to preserve and promote traditional culinary values, acquire world cuisine elite;

2. Investing and building shopping streets, shopping centers, chains of goods trading shops, souvenirs, handicrafts with domestic origin, duty -free shops;organize annual promotions;

3. Investment in developing tourism services associated with sports on the basis of tourism resources and terrain advantages of Vietnam;organize sporting events to attract tourists;

4. Building and organizing traditional and contemporary performing art programs;connect the museum system and theater with tourism activities;exploiting folk games, traditional festivals that attract tourists;Building theme parks and entertainment centers;

5. Providing health services, health care, beauty care on the basis of exploiting traditional medicine and modern medicine values;

6. Provide other relevant services according to the needs of tourists and in accordance with the law.

Tour guide, tour guide card
1. Tour guide includes international tour guide, domestic tour guide and tour guide at the point.

2. The practice scope of the tour guide is prescribed as follows:

a) International tour guides are guided for domestic tourists and international tourists to Vietnam nationwide and bring tourists abroad;

b) Domestic tour guides are guided for domestic tourists who are Vietnamese citizens nationwide;

c) Tour guide at the point is guided for tourists within the tourist area and tourist destinations.

3. Conditions for practicing tour guide include:

a) Having a tour guide card;

b) Having a labor contract with a business business business, a tourist guide service provider or a member of the social and professional organization on tour guides for travel guidesInternational calendar and domestic tour guide;

c) Having a guiding contract with a travel service business or a written assignment to guide the tourism program;For tour guides at the point, there must be a assignment of organizations and individuals managing tourist resorts and tourist destinations.

4. Tour guide cards include international tour guide cards, domestic tour guide cards and tour guide cards at the point.

International tour guide cards and domestic tour guide cards are 5 years.

5. The appraisal fee for granting tour guide cards shall comply with the law on fees and fees.

Conditions for granting tour guide cards
1. Conditions for issuance of domestic tour guide cards include:

a) Having Vietnamese nationality and permanent residence in Vietnam;

b) Having full civil act capacity;

c) Do not suffer from infectious diseases, do not use narcotics;

d) Graduated from intermediate or higher, specialized in travel guidance;In case of high school or higher graduation, there must be a certificate of domestic tourism guidance.

2. Conditions for granting international tour guide cards include:

a) Conditions specified at Points a, b and c, Clause 1 of this Article;

b) Graduated from college or higher in tourism guidance;In case of graduating from a college or higher specialty, there must be a certificate of international tourism guidance;

c) Proficient use of foreign language registration.

3. Conditions for granting tour guide cards at the point include:

a) Conditions specified at Points a, b and c, Clause 1 of this Article;

b) To meet the requirements of professional inspection of tourism guidance at the point organized by the provincial -level tourism specialized agencies.

4. The Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism details the card samples, training, fostering, organizing exams and granting professional travel guidance certificates;Content of professional travel guidance at the point;Performing standard of foreign languages.

Records, order, procedures, authority to issue international tour guide cards, domestic tour guide cards
1. Application for issuance of international tour guide cards, domestic tour guide cards include:

a) Application for granting tour guides in the form set by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Resume certified by the People's Committee of the commune at the residence;

c) Certified copies of diplomas and certificates corresponding to the conditions specified at Point d, Clause 1 or Point b and Point c, Clause 2, Article 59 of this Law;

d) Health certificate issued by a competent medical examination and treatment establishment within a period of not exceeding 06 months up to the time of submission;

d) 02 color portrait photos of 3 cm x 4 cm.

2. The order, procedures, authority to issue international tour guide cards, domestic tour guide cards are prescribed as follows:

a) The person who proposes to issue a tour guide card submit 01 dossier to the provincial tourism specialized agency;

b) Within 15 days from the date of receipt of a valid dossier, the provincial -level specialized agency granting a tour guide card to the proposed person;In case of refusal, must reply in writing and specify the reason.

Profile, order, procedure, authority to issue a tour guide card at the point
1. The application for the grant of tour guide cards at the point includes:

a) Application for granting tour guides in the form set by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Documents specified at Points b, d and dd, Clause 1, Article 60 of this Law.

2. The order, procedures and authority to issue a tour guide card at the point are prescribed as follows:

a) Provincial -level tourism specialized agencies annually announce plans to organize professional inspection of tourist guidance at the point;

b) The person who proposes to issue a tour guide card at the point of submission of 01 set of dossiers to the provincial tourism specialized agency;

c) Provincial -level tourism specialized agencies organize the inspection and grant of tour guides at the point for the person who meets the requirements of professional inspection within 10 days from the date of inspection results.

Cassing the tour guide card
1. International tour guides, domestic tourist guides carry out procedures to request the exchange of tour guide cards when the card expires.

2. The application for exchange of tour guide cards includes:

a) Application for exchange of tour guides in the form set by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Documents specified at Points b, d and dd, Clause 1, Article 60 of this Law;

c) Certified copy of the certificate that has been updated with knowledge update to tour guides issued by competent state agencies;

d) The tour guide card has been issued.

3. The order and procedures for granting tour guide cards are prescribed as follows:

a) The person who proposes to change the tour guide card submit 01 dossier to the competent state agency to issue the card;

b) Within 10 days from the date of receipt of a valid dossier, the competent state agency granted the card shall grant tour guides to the proposed person;In case of refusal, must reply in writing and specify the reason.

4. The Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism details detailing the knowledge update of knowledge and certificates of knowledge updating knowledge for international tourist guides and domestic tourist guides.

Reward tour guide card
1. Tour guide cards are re -issued in case of loss, damage or change of information on the card.The deadline for the tour guide card is re -issued by the remaining term of the granted card.

2. The application for re -issuance of a tour guide card includes:

a) Application for re -granting tour guide cards according to the form prescribed by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) 02 color portrait photos of 3 cm x 4 cm;

c) Certified copy of papers related to the content changes in case of re -grant of the card due to changing information on the tour guide card.

3. The order and procedures for re -issuance of tour guide cards are prescribed as follows:

a) The person who proposes to re -issue a tour guide card shall submit 01 dossier to the competent state agency to issue the card;

b) Within 10 days from the date of receiving a valid dossier, the competent state agency will re -issue a tour guide card to the proposed person;In case of refusal to reply in writing and specify the reason.

Revoke the tour guide card
1. The tour guide card is recovered in case the tour guide has one of the following acts:

a) Harming national sovereignty and interests, national defense and security;

b) For other individuals to use tour guide cards to practice;

c) Do not meet the conditions of practice, the conditions for granting tour guide cards in accordance with this Law;

d) Forging dossiers for granting, renewing and re -granting tour guide cards.

2. The competent state agency granting a tour guide card decided to revoke the tour guide card and publicly announced on the website of the tour guide manager of the Vietnam National Administration of Tourism andCard recovery agency.

3. The tour guide that has been revoked the card is only requested to request a competent state agency to issue a tour guide card after 12 months from the date of being recovered.

Rights and obligations of tour guides
1. Tour guide has the following right:

a) Participate in social and professional organization on tourism guidance;

b) Receive other salaries and remuneration under the contract;

c) Participate in training courses on knowledge, expertise, skills, and travel practicing skills;

d) In case of emergency or force majeure, the right to change the tourism program, adjust the standards and services of tourists.

2. Tour guides have the following obligations:

a) Guide tourists according to the assigned tasks or under the guiding contract;

b) Compliance with tourists to comply with Vietnamese laws, laws of tourism destinations, rules where to visit;respect local customs and practices;

c) Information for tourists about tourism programs, services and legitimate rights and interests of tourists;

d) Guide tourists in accordance with the tourism program, with a civilized, dedicated and thoughtful attitude with tourists;Report to the travel business service business decision to change the tourism program in case the tourist requires;

d) Be responsible for assistance in ensuring the safety of life, health and property of tourists;

e) Participate in the knowledge update course as prescribed in Clause 4, Article 62 of this Law;

g) Wearing a tour guide card while practicing travel guidance;

h) International tour guide and domestic tour guide must carry papers assigning the tasks of enterprises to organize tourism programs and tourism programs in Vietnamese while practicing.In case of guiding international tourists, the tour guide must bring the tourism program in Vietnamese and foreign languages.

Establishing a representative office in Vietnam of foreign tourism agencies, international and regional tourism organizations
1. Foreign tourism agencies, international and regional tourism organizations established representative offices in Vietnam.

2. The application for the establishment of a representative office must be consular legalization, including:

a) Application for establishing a representative office according to the form prescribed by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Decision on establishing foreign tourism agencies, international and regional tourism organizations;

c) Decision to establish a representative office of foreign tourism agencies, international and regional tourism organizations;

d) Decision to appoint the head of the representative office.

3. The order and procedures for establishing a representative office in Vietnam are prescribed as follows:

a) The head of the representative office shall submit 01 set of dossiers to the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Within 30 days from the date of receiving a valid dossier, the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism evaluate and submit to the Prime Minister for consideration and decision;

c) Within 05 working days from the date of receiving the opinion of the Prime Minister, the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism notify in writing to the head of the representative office.

Establishing tourism development support fund
1. Tourism development assistance fund is a budget foreign financial fund, with legal status, seals and separate accounts, established by the Prime Minister, approving the Regulation on organization and operation..

2. Tourism development assistance fund is exempted from tax payment and payments of the state budget in accordance with the law.

3. Tourism development support fund is formed from the following sources:

a) Charter capital issued by the state budget;

b) The state budget adds an annual supplement deducted from the source of sightseeing fee, visa issuance fee and papers related to exit and entering Vietnam to foreigners;

c) Source of voluntary and legitimate contributions of domestic and foreign enterprises, organizations and individuals;

d) Other legitimate revenues as prescribed by law.

4. The Government details Clause 3 of this Article.

State management responsibility for tourism of the Government
1. The Government unified state management of tourism.

2. The Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism is the focal agency to help the Government carry out the state management of tourism and have the following tasks and powers:

a) Promulgate or submit to the competent state agency for promulgation and organize the implementation of tourism legal documents;tourism development strategy, planning, planning and policies;List of potential locations for national tourist area development;

b) Coordinate and link inter -country, inter -regional and inter -provincial tourism activities;

c) Develop national standards, national technical regulations on tourism;Building tourism management databases;

d) Coordinate with relevant agencies, social and professional organizations on tourism and law education on tourism;

d) Organize and manage training and retraining of tourism human resources;research and application of science and technology in the field of tourism;Guidance on electronic transactions in the field of tourism;

e) Organize surveys and evaluation of tourism resources;

g) Implementing international cooperation on tourism;tourism promotion activities in the country and abroad;

h) Manage and organize the granting and revocation of licenses, tour guide cards and other certification documents on tourism activities;

i) Socialization of investment activities, development of tourism products, tourism promotion, training and retraining of tourism human resources;

k) Checking, inspecting, settling complaints, denunciations and handling violations of tourism laws.

State management responsibility for tourism of the People's Committees at all levels
1. The provincial People's Committee, within the scope of its tasks and powers, performs the state management of tourism in the locality;Concretize the strategies, plannings, plans and policies for tourism development in accordance with local reality.

2. The People's Committees at all levels have the following tasks and powers:

a) Promulgate or submit to the competent state agency to promulgate preferential policies and attract investments to exploit the potential and strengths of local tourism;support for community tourism development;

b) Manage tourism resources, tourist areas, tourist destinations, tourism business activities and tourist guidance in the area;

c) Ensuring security, social order and safety, environment and food safety at the tourist area, tourist destinations, where many tourists are gathered;

d) Propagate and raise people's awareness to ensure a friendly, healthy and civilized tourism environment;

d) Organize the arrangement of stops and parking for vehicles that have been granted signboards of tourist transportation signs to access tourist attractions and tourist accommodation establishments;organize the review and installation of signs and signs to the tourist area and tourist destinations;

e) Organize the reception and resolution of tourists;

g) Perform other duties as prescribed by this Law.

The authority of the district court

The district court resolves according to the first instance procedures for the following complaints:

1. Complaints of administrative decisions, administrative acts of state administrative agencies from district or less at the same scope of administrative boundaries with Courts or competent people in such state administrative agencies, except for administrative decisions and administrative acts of district -level People's Committees and presidents of district -level People's Committees;

2. Disciplinary lawsuits forced the job of the head of the agency or organization from the district or less at the same scope of the administrative boundaries with the Court for civil servants under the management of agencies and groupsthat position;

3. Complainting the voters' list of the agency to make a list of voters on the same scope of administrative boundaries with the Court.

The authority of the provincial Court

The provincial court resolves according to the first instance procedures for the following complaints:

1. Complaints of administrative decisions, administrative acts of ministries, ministerial -level agencies, government -attached agencies, President's Office, National Assembly Office, State Audit, Supreme People's Court,The Supreme People's Procuracy and administrative decisions, administrative acts of the competent person in that agency that the petitioner has a place of residence, workplace or headquarters on the same scope of administrative boundaries withCourt;In case the petitioner has no residence, workplace or headquarters on the territory of Vietnam, the authority to settle the Court where the agency or person competent authority issues administrative decisions, has administrative acts;

2. Complaints of administrative decisions, administrative acts of agencies belonging to one of the state agencies specified in Clause 1 of this Article and administrative decisions, administrative acts of the competent person in that agency.but the petitioner has a place of residence, workplace or headquarters on the same scope of administrative boundaries with the Court;In case the petitioner has no residence, workplace or headquarters on the territory of Vietnam, the authority to settle the Court where the agency or person competent authority issues administrative decisions, has administrative acts;

3. Complaints of administrative decisions and administrative acts of provincial -level state agencies within the same administrative boundaries with the Court and competent persons in such state agencies;

4. Complaints of administrative decisions and administrative acts of district -level People's Committees and presidents of district -level People's Committees on the same scope of administrative boundaries with the Court;

5. Complaints of administrative decisions, administrative acts of representative agencies of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam abroad or of competent persons in that agency where the petitioner has a place of residence inSame administrative boundaries with the Court;In case the petitioner has no residence in Vietnam, the competent court is the Hanoi People's Court or the Ho Chi Minh City People's Court;

6. Disciplinary lawsuits forced the resignation of the heads of agencies, provincial -level organizations, ministries and central branches that the petitioner has a workplace when being disciplined on the same scope of administrative boundaries with the Courtsentence;

7. Complaints decision to settle complaints about the decision to handle the competition case that the petitioner has a place of residence, workplace or headquarters on the same scope of administrative boundaries with the Court;

8. In case of necessity, the provincial Court may be taken to resolve the administrative case under the jurisdiction of the district court according to the provisions of Article 31 of this Law.

