The duties and powers of the examiner

When assigned by the Chief Justice of the Court, the examiner has the following tasks and powers:

1. Examining the administrative case file that the judgment and decision of the Court has taken legal effect should be reviewed according to the procedures for cassation and re -examination;

2. Conclusion on the verification and reporting of the results of verification and proposal of a plan to resolve administrative cases with the Chief Justice of the Court;

3. Collecting documents and evidence in accordance with this Law;

4. Perform other duties and powers in accordance with this Law.

Tasks and powers of the Court Secretary

When assigned, the Court Secretary has the following tasks and powers:

1. Preparing the necessary professional work before opening the trial;

2. Disseminate the trial rules;

3. Checking and reporting to the Trial panel of the list of people summoned to the trial;

4. Record the records of the trial, the meeting record, the minutes of taking the testimony of participants in the proceedings;

5. Perform other duties and powers in accordance with this Law.

Duties and powers of the Director of the Procuracy

1. When carrying out the control of law compliance in administrative proceedings, the Procuracy has the following tasks and powers:

a) Organizing and directing the inspection of law compliance in administrative proceedings;

b) The decision to assign procurators to supervise the compliance with the law in administrative proceedings, participate in the trial, the meeting to resolve the administrative case in accordance with this Law and notify the CourtThe case;assigning the inspection to conduct procedurals for administrative cases to ensure the principles prescribed in Article 14 of this Law;

c) Decision on changing procurators and inspectors;

d) Prestige according to the appellate procedure, cassation, re -examination of judgments and decisions of the Court in accordance with this Law;

d) Requirements and recommendations as prescribed by this Law;

e) Settling complaints and denunciations in accordance with this Law;

g) Perform other duties and powers in accordance with this Law.

2. When the Director is absent, a Deputy Director is authorized by the Director to perform the duties and powers of the Director, except for the right to decide the appeal specified at Point d, Clause 1 of this Article.The Deputy Director is responsible to the Director for performing the tasks and powers authorized.

