The tenderness when arguing

1. After the end of the question, the argument at the trial is done as follows:

a) The defender of the lawsuit of the petitioner presented.The petitioner has the right to supplement his opinion.In cases where agencies and organizations initiate lawsuits, representatives of agencies and organizations present their opinions;

b) The defending the legitimate rights and interests of the person who is sued and responded.The sued person has the right to supplement their opinions;

c) Persons defending the legitimate rights and interests of the person with related rights and obligations presented.People with related rights and obligations have the right to supplement their opinions;

d) The litigants respond to the control of the presiding judge;

dd) When deeming it necessary, the Trial panel may ask the parties to argue additionally on specific issues as a basis for solving the case.

2. In case the petitioner, the lawsuit, the person with the rights and related obligations without the defending their legitimate rights and interests, they present themselves when arguing.

3. In case of absence from one of the parties, the defense of the litigant's legitimate rights and interests and other participants, the presiding judge must publish their testimony, the document to protect the rights.And the legal interests of the involved parties, on the basis of that, the litigants present at the trial of debate and respond.

Deliberation

1. After finishing the debate, the Trial panel entered the deliberation room for the deliberation.

2. Only members of the Trial panel have the right to delegate.When the deliberation, the members of the Trial Panel must solve all the problems of the case by voting in the majority of each issue.The people's jurors voted first, the judge voted final.In case the trial panel consists of 05 members, the judge presiding over the trial is the last voter.People with minority opinions have the right to present their opinions in writing and be included in the case file.

3. When the deliberation, the trial panel is only based on documents and evidence that have been inspected and reviewed at the trial, the results of the litigation at the trial, the opinion of the procurator, the regulations, the regulations.of the law and research, applying administrative law (if any) to decide on the following issues:

a) The legality and basis of the form and content of the administrative decision or the implementation of administrative acts are sued;

b) The legality of competence, order and procedures for promulgating administrative decisions or the implementation of administrative acts;

c) The statute of limitations and terms of the issuance of administrative decisions or committing administrative acts;

d) The connection between administrative decisions, administrative acts and the legitimate rights and interests of the lawsuits and related people;

d) Legal and basis of relevant administrative documents (if any);

e) The problem of compensation for damage and other issues (if any).

4. When the deliberation must have a record of the discussion and decision of the Trial panel.The minutes of the deliberation must be signed by the Trial Panel members in the deliberation room before the sentence.

5. In case the case has many complicated circumstances, the deliberation requires more time, the trial panel may decide to extend the deliberation time, but not more than 05 working days after the end of the end.End debate at the trial.

The trial panel must notify those present at the trial and participants of the proceedings at the trial to know the date, time and place of sentence;If the Trial Panel has made the notice and a participant in the proceedings, the Trial panel still conducts the sentence in accordance with Article 195 of this Law.

The authority of the Trial panel

1. The trial panel considers the legality of administrative decisions, administrative acts, disciplinary decisions forced jobs, decisions to settle complaints about the decision to handle the competition case, the list of votersBeing sued, decisions to settle complaints and relevant legal documents.

2. The trial panel has the right to decide:

a) Uncle asked to sue, if that request, there is no legal basis;

b) Accept part or all requests to initiate a lawsuit, cancel part or all of the illegal administrative decisions and decide on the settlement of relevant complaints (if any);forcing state agencies or competent people in state agencies to perform tasks and official duties in accordance with the law;at the same time, propose the way to handle illegal administrative decisions has been canceled;

c) Accept part or all of the request for lawsuits and declaration of administrative acts is against the law, cancel part or all the decisions to settle the relevant complaints (if any);forcing state agencies or competent people in the farming agency to terminate illegal administrative acts;

d) Accepting the request to sue and cancel the disciplinary decision forced to resign the law;forcing heads of agencies and organizations to perform tasks and official duties in accordance with the law;

d) Accept part or all requests to initiate a lawsuit, cancel part or all decisions to settle complaints about the decision to handle the case of illegal competition;forcing agencies and persons to issue a decision to settle complaints about the decision to handle the competition to resolve the case in accordance with the Competition Law;

e) Accept a part or the entire request to initiate a lawsuit;forcing the agency to make a list of voters amending and supplementing the list of voters in accordance with the law;

g) Forcing agencies and organizations to compensate for damage, restore the legitimate rights and interests of agencies, organizations and individuals infringed upon due to administrative decisions, administrative acts, disciplinary decisions forced severitythe work and decision to handle the case of illegal competition caused;

h) To propose to the competent state agency, the head of the competent state agency to consider the responsibilities of the state agencies and the competent persons of the state agencies.

3. In case of a competent agency or person to consider and handle administrative documents related to administrative decisions, administrative acts that are sued as prescribed in Clause 1, Article 6 of this Law, thenThe trial panel reports to the Chief Justice of the Court that is resolving such a case that requires a written request to the agency and person competent to consider and handle that administrative document.In this case, the Trial panel has the right to suspend the trial to wait for the settlement results of the competent agencies and people.Within 30 days from the date of receiving the Court's decision, the competent authorities and persons must reply in writing the results of the Court to know as a basis for the settlement of the case.Past this time limit without receiving a written response from the agency or person competent, the Trial panel has the right to apply the document of the superior state management agency to decide as prescribed in Clause 2This.

4. In case of detecting legal documents related to the settlement of administrative cases that show signs against the constitution, laws, legal documents of superior state agencies, the CouncilThe trial temporarily suspended the trial as prescribed in Article 112 of this Law.

Procuracy decision decision

1. The decision of the Procuracy's protest must be written in writing and have the following main contents:

a) Date, month and year issue decisions for protest and number of protest decisions;

b) The name of the Procuracy issued a decision to protest;

c) Of which or part of the judgment or decision of the first -instance court has not taken legal effect;

d) Reasons and grounds of the Procuracy's protest and request;

d) Full name of the person who signed the decision to protest and seal of the Procuracy issued a decision to protest.

2. The decision to protest must be sent immediately to the first -instance court issued a judgment or decision to be protested so that the first -instance court to carry out the procedures prescribed in Article 216 of this Law.Attached to the protest decision is an additional document and evidence (if any) to prove the Procuracy's appeal is grounded and legal.

In case the appellate trial panel does not have to open the trial, not to summon the litigant

1. The appellate trial panel does not have to open the trial in the following cases:

a) Considering the appeal and overdue appeal;

b) The case specified in Clause 2, Article 209 of this Law;Considering the appeal and protest on the charges;

c) Considering the appeal and protests of the first -instance court decisions.

2. In case of Clause 1 of this Article, the Trial panel does not have to summon the litigant, except for the case of overdue appeal specified in Clause 2, Article 208 of this Law or should hear their opinions.If the summoned person is absent, the Court still conducts the meeting.

Suspension of appellate trial of the case

1. The appellate court issued a decision to suspend the appellate trial of the case in the following cases:

a) The case specified at Point a, Clause 1, Article 143 of this Law;

b) In case of returning the appeal application in accordance with this Law, the Appellate Court has accepted the case file;

c) The appealed person withdraws the entire appeal or the Procuracy withdraws the entire protest;

d) The appeal person is summoned for the second time but still
Absent, except for cases where they requested the Court to be absent or in case of force majeure events, objective obstacles;

d) Other cases that law have.

2. In case the appealed person withdraws the entire appeal or the Procuracy withdraws the entire appeal before the appellate court issues a decision to bring the case to the appellate trial, the judge is assigned to preside over the trial.decision to suspend appellate trial;In case the appealed person withdraws the entire appeal, the Procuracy withdraws the entire appeal after the appellate court issues a decision to bring the case to the appellate trial, the appellate trial panel issues a decision to suspendAppeal hearing.

In these cases, the first instance judgment and decision takes legal effect from the date the appellate court issues a decision to suspend appellate trial.

3. In case the appealed person withdraws a part of the appeal or the Procuracy withdraws a part of the appeal, the appellate trial panel judges the appeal of the appeal to the part of the appeal, the Procuracy partially withdraws the protest andThe decision to suspend the trial of that appeal and appeal in the appellate judgment.

4. In case the Trial Council suspends the appellate trial according to the provisions of Clause 2 of this Article, the judgment and decision of the first -instance Court is one of the cases specified in Clause 1, Article 255of this law must propose to the Chief Justice of the competent court to consider according to the cassation procedure.

5. The decision to suspend must be sent immediately to the litigants and the Procuracy of the same level.

Postponed the appellate trial

1. Cases of postponing the trial:

a) Cases specified in Clause 2, Article 161, Clause 3 and Clause 4, Article 223, Clause 1, Article 225 of this Law;

b) Members of the Trial Panel, Procurator, Secretary of the trial, interpreter were changed without a replacement immediately;

c) The assessor is changed;

d) It is necessary to verify and collect additional documents and evidence that cannot be implemented at the trial.

2. In case of postponing the trial prescribed in Clause 2, Article 159 and Clause 2, Article 160 of this Law.

3. The time limit for postponing the trial and the decision to postpone the appellate trial shall comply with the provisions of Article 163 of this Law.

Debate at the appellate trial

1. At the appellate trial, the litigant, the defense of the litigant's legitimate rights and interests can only argue about issues within the scope of appellate trial and have been asked at the appellate trial.

2. The self -outing process is performed as follows:

a) The defending the legitimate rights and interests of the appealed person presented.Appeals have the right to supplement their opinions;

b) Persons who defend the legal rights and interests of the litigants debate and respond.The involved parties have the right to supplement their opinions;

c) The litigants respond to the control of the presiding judge;

d) When deeming it necessary, the trial panel may ask the parties to argue additionally on specific issues as a basis for solving the case.

3. The order of debate for the Procuracy's protest was carried out as follows:

a) The person who defends the litigant's legitimate rights and interests on the legality and properties are grounded for the Procuracy's protest.The involved parties have the right to supplement their opinions;

b) Procurators express their opinions on issues that defenders of the litigant's legitimate rights and interests have stated.

4. In case the involved parties have no defenders of their legitimate rights and interests, they argue themselves.

5. In case of absence from one of the parties and other participants, the presiding judge must announce their testimony so that the litigants are present at the trial of debate and responding.

Conditions to apply shortened procedures

1. The case is resolved according to the shortened procedure when there are all the following conditions:

a) The case has simple circumstances, documents, complete and clear evidence, ensuring sufficient grounds to resolve the case and the Court does not have to collect documents and evidence;

b) The litigants have clear addresses and headquarters;

c) There is no litigant residing abroad, except for cases where the litigants overseas have agreed with the litigants in Vietnam to request the Court to settle according to the shortened procedures.

2. In the process of resolving the case on a shortened procedure, the Court issues a decision to transfer the case to a normal procedure if one of the following cases:

a) The generation of new details that the involved parties do not agree and need to verify and collect more documents and evidence or need to conduct an assessment;

b) It is necessary to pricing assets if the litigants do not agree on prices;

c) It is necessary to apply temporary emergency measures;

d) The person has relevant rights and obligations;

dd) arise independent requirements;

e) generating litigants residing abroad that need to carry out judicial entrustment, unless the case specified at Point c, Clause 1 of this Article.

3. In case of transferring the case to resolution according to normal procedures, the time limit for preparation for trial is recalculated from the date of issuance of a decision to transfer the case to resolution according to normal procedures.

