The judgment trial panel issued a decision to cancel the legally effective judgment or decision to be protested for the first instance trial or re -appellate trial in the following cases:

1. The collection of evidence and proving not fully or improperly provided in Chapter VI of this Law;

2. Conclusion in the judgments and decisions that are not suitable for the objective circumstances of the case or have serious mistakes in applying the law;

3. The composition of the first instance trial panel or appellate is not in accordance with this law or has other serious violations of the proceeding procedures.

