Film production activities in Vietnam of foreign organizations and individuals

1. Foreign organizations and individuals producing films in Vietnam must use film production services provided by Vietnamese film facilities.

2. Foreign organizations and individuals using film production services in Vietnam must ensure the following conditions:

a) There is a written agreement or contract to provide film production services with Vietnamese film facilities;

b) Films using film production services in Vietnam do not violate the provisions of Article 9 of this Law;

c) In case of using the filming service using the context in Vietnam, the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism is granted a license to provide filming services using the context in Vietnam.

3. Dossiers of application for licenses to provide filming services to use the context in Vietnam to foreign organizations and individuals including:

a) The written request for licensing according to the form is prescribed by the Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) The scenario of the film summary and detailed script The content of the filming using the context in Vietnam in Vietnamese;

c) A written agreement or contract to provide filming services using the context in Vietnam with foreign organizations and individuals;

d) The written commitment does not violate the provisions of Article 9 of this Law of foreign organizations and individuals using filming services to use the context in Vietnam.

4. The order and procedures for granting licenses to provide filming services to use the context in Vietnam to foreign organizations and individuals are prescribed as follows:

a) Foreign organizations and individuals use the filming service to use the context in Vietnam or Vietnamese film facilities to provide filming services to use the context in Vietnam for foreign organizations and individuals.submit 01 set of documents via national public service portal or by post or submit directly to the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism;

b) Within 20 days from the date of receiving a complete and valid dossier, the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism shall issue a license;In case of not granting permits to reply in writing and specify the reason.

In case the scenario must be amended by violations specified in Article 9 of this Law and other provisions of the relevant law or the dossier must be amended and supplemented with information at the request of the Ministry of Culture and Sports.And travel, within 20 days from the date of receiving the script that has corrected the content or dossier that has been amended and fully supplemented with information, the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism implements a license.

5. In case of changing the content specified at Points a, b and c, Clause 3 of this Article after being granted a license to provide filming services to use the context in Vietnam, foreign organizations and individualsor Vietnamese film facilities must implement the request for re -issuance of licenses according to the order and procedures specified in Clause 4 of this Article;Except for the case of changing the content specified at Points a and c, Clause 3 of this Article, within 05 working days from the date of receiving a complete and valid dossier, the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism shall issue a certificatemagic.

6. The Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism decided to revoke the license to provide filming services using the context in Vietnam in the following cases:

a) Violating the provisions of Article 9 of this Law in the film production process:

b) Information in the application for a license is fake;

c) Failing to comply with the license content.

