Responsibilities of the Government

The Government unified state management of young people and the following responsibilities:

1. Ensuring the effectiveness and effectiveness of the implementation of the contents of state management of youth;

2. Ensuring mechanisms and measures to coordinate among ministries, ministerial -level agencies, government -attached agencies, local authorities and relevant agencies and organizations in formulating and implementing policies and policies,law for young people;

3. Ensuring the construction and implementation of youth development goals and targets in the strategy, programs and plans for socio -economic development long -term, medium and annual and annual national, branches and fields,;

4. Report the results of implementing policies and laws to young people at the request of the National Assembly.

Responsibility of the Ministry of Home Affairs

The Ministry of Home Affairs is responsible to the Government to perform the state management of young people and have the following responsibilities:

1. Promulgating according to its competence or submitting to competent state agencies for promulgation of youth policies and laws;Youth development strategies, programs and plans;

2. Proposing the integration of policies, targets and goals of youth development when developing policies, strategies, programs and socio -economic development plans of the industry and field.Guide ministries and branches to integrate statistics on Vietnamese youth into the system of ministries and branches;

3. To guide ministries, ministerial -level agencies and provincial -level People's Committees to perform state management tasks on youth;organize training and fostering knowledge and skills for cadres and civil servants working in the state management of young people;

4. To assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with relevant agencies, manage, exploit and publish data on youth and youth development index;

5. To assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with ministries, ministerial -level agencies, government -attached agencies and the Central Youth Union of Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union to formulate and organize the implementation of policies and laws for young people;

6. Checking, inspecting and settling complaints, denunciations and petitions;preliminary, summarizing, emulation and commendation;handling violations according to their competence or proposing competent agencies, organizations and individuals to handle violations in the implementation of policies and laws for young people;

7. Annually, report to the Government results of implementing policies and laws for young people and the task of state management of young people;

8. Assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with relevant agencies, manage international cooperation activities on youth in accordance with the law.

Responsibilities of ministries and ministerial agencies

The ministries, ministerial -level agencies, within the scope of their duties and powers, coordinate with the Ministry of Home Affairs to perform the state management of young people and have the following responsibilities:

1. Promulgating policies and mechanisms for young people to participate in development programs of sectors and fields;

2. Integrating policies, targets and goals of youth development when developing policies, strategies, programs and socio -economic development plans of the industry and field;Integrating statistical indicators of Vietnamese youth into the system of ministries and branches;

3. To guide the provincial People's Committee to implement policies and laws for young people under the competence of state management of branches and fields;

4. Annually, report the implementation of policies and laws to young people by branches and fields and send to the Ministry of Home Affairs for summarizing and reporting to the Government.

Responsibilities of the People's Council, the provincial People's Committee

1. The provincial People's Council, within the scope of their duties and powers, has the following responsibility:

a) Promulgate a resolution on local youth development to implement the State's policies and laws to young people;

b) Decide on the targets and goals of youth development in the local socio -economic development resolution every year and each period;

c) Decision to allocate budget estimates to organize the implementation of policies, laws, strategies, programs and plans to develop youth in the locality;

d) Supervise the implementation of policies and laws for young people in the locality;

d) The payroll decision of the agency assigned to perform the state management tasks on youth.

2. The provincial People's Committee, within the scope of their duties and powers, perform the state management of young people and have the following responsibilities:

a) Organize the implementation of policies, laws, strategies, programs and plans to develop young people in the locality;

b) Integrating the youth development targets and goals when developing the annual and each stages of socio -economic development programs and plans every stage;

c) Building a contingent of cadres and civil servants in charge of state management of young people;

d) Ensuring the legitimate and legitimate rights and interests of young people when investing in developing educational, health, health counseling, cultural, physical and sports activities;

d) Manage, exploit and publish statistical data on youth, local youth development index;

e) Perform statistical and information work, annually report the results of the implementation of policies and laws on youth and send to the Ministry of Home Affairs for summarizing and reporting to the Government;

g) Checking, inspecting, handling violations, settling complaints, denunciations and recommendations on young people;

h) Direct and guide subordinate People's Committees to perform the task of state management of young people.
